{DIALOGUE}: So what's the deal?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: My mission is to protect you.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Yeah?
{DIALOGUE}: Who sent you?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: You did.
{DIALOGUE}: Thirty years from now you reprogrammed me to be your protector here, in this time.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John gives him an amazed look.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: This is deep.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 50 EXT. STREET - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John and Terminator on the bike again, weaving through the side streets.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They blend into the evening traffic.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In the darkness, Terminator's wounds are not readily visible.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John cranes his head up and back.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: So this other guy?
{DIALOGUE}: He's a terminator too, right, like you?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: Not like me.
{DIALOGUE}: A T-1000.
{DIALOGUE}: Advanced prototype.
{DIALOGUE}: A mimetic polyalloy.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: What does that mean?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: Liquid metal.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Radical.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: You are targeted for termination.
{DIALOGUE}: The T-1000 will not stop until it complete its mission.
{DIALOGUE}: Ever.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John mulls that over.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Where we going?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: We have to leave the city, immediately.
{DIALOGUE}: And avoid the authorities.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Can I stop by my house?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: Negative.
{DIALOGUE}: The T-1000 will definitely try to reacquire you there.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: You sure?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: I would.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 51 EXT. PAYPHONE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John is quickly going through his pockets for change.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He has plenty of bills but no quarters.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Look, Todd and Janelle are dicks but I gotta warn them.
{DIALOGUE}: Shit!
{DIALOGUE}: You got a quarter?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator reaches past John and smashes the cover plate off the phone's cash box with the heel of his hand.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A shower of change tumbles out.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator hands one to John.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John dials.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 52 INT. VOIGHT HOUSE - KITCHEN - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Janelle Voight picks up the kitchen phone and cradles it with her shoulder which she continues to chop vegetables with a large knife.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She answers sweetly.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JANELLE
{DIALOGUE}: Hello?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{META_DATA}: (filtered through phone)
{DIALOGUE}: Janelle?
{DIALOGUE}: It's me.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In the backyard, John's German Shepherd is going bonkers, barking at something.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JANELLE
{DIALOGUE}: John?
{DIALOGUE}: Where are you, honey?
{DIALOGUE}: It's late.
{DIALOGUE}: You should come home, dear.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm making a casserole.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: AT THE PAYPHONE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John listens, an odd look on his face.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He covers the phone's mouthpiece and turns to Terminator.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{META_DATA}: (whispering)
{DIALOGUE}: Something's wrong.
{DIALOGUE}: She's never this nice.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IN THE VOIGHTS' KITCHEN.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Todd comes through the kitchen's back door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Just home from work.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He ignores Janelle and opens the fridge.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Grabs a carton of milk.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Takes a sip.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frowns at the dog's barking.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TODD
{DIALOGUE}: What the hell's the goddamn dog barking at?
{DIALOGUE}: SHUT UP, YOU MUTT!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TIGHT ON JANELLE as Todd growls around the kitchen behind her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He passes OUT OF FRAME next to her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Janelle switches the phone to her other hand then... THUNK!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her free hand seems to do something out of frame.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There is a gurgling, and the sound of liquid dribbling onto the floor.
{META_DATA}: (Don't go away.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We'll find out what happened in a moment)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: AT THE PAYPHONE
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: The dog's really barking.
{DIALOGUE}: Maybe it's already there.
{DIALOGUE}: What should I do?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator takes the phone from John's hand.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Janelle's voice is floating through the receiver.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JANELLE
{META_DATA}: (filtered)
{DIALOGUE}: John?
{DIALOGUE}: John, are you okay?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator speaks into the phone in a perfect imitation of John's voice...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{META_DATA}: (in John's voice)
{DIALOGUE}: I'm right here.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm fine.
{META_DATA}: (to John, a whisper)
{DIALOGUE}: What's the dog's name?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Max.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator nods.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Speaks into the phone.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: Hey, Janelle, what's wrong with Wolfy?
{DIALOGUE}: I can hear him barking.
{DIALOGUE}: Is he okay?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JANELLE
{META_DATA}: (filtered)
{DIALOGUE}: Wolfy's fine, honey.
{DIALOGUE}: Where are you?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator unceremoniously hangs up the phone.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Turns to John.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: Your foster parents are dead.
{DIALOGUE}: Let's go.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator heads for the bike.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John, shocked, stares after him.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 53 INT. VOIGHT HOUSE/KITCHEN
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Janelle hangs up the phone.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her expression is neutral.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Calm.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: PAN OVER along her arm, which is stretched out straight from the shoulder.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Partway along its length her arm has turned smoothly into something else... a metal cylinder which tapers into a sword-like spike.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Now we see Todd Voight PINNED TO A KITCHEN CABINET by the spike which has punched through his milk carton, through his mouth and exits the back of his head into the cabinet door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His eyes are glassy and lifeless.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The spike is withdrawn -- SWIISHHTT!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: -- so rapidly, Todd is actually standing there a second before he slumps out of sight.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THUMP.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 53A Janelle doesn't bat an eye as the spike smoothly changes shape and color, transforming back into a hand, and then...
{META_DATA}: 53B JANELLE CHANGES rapidly into the COP we now know as the T-1000. The
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: change has liquid quality.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: T-1000 opens the back door.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 54 EXT. VOIGHT HOUSE/BACKYARD - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: T-1000 approaches the big German Shepherd, which slinks away from it, barking in fear.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: T-1000 walk right into CLOSE UP.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reaches down, OUT OF FRAME.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We hear that sickening THUNK followed by a shrill YELP.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then T-1000's hand snaps up INTO FRAME holding a bloody dog collar.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The tag reads "MAX".
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: T-1000 nods thoughtfully.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Heads back to the house.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 55 EXT. PARKING LOT - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dark.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Off a quiet street.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator stands near the Harley, watching John pace before him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John's brain is calling time-out.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: This is all too weird.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: I need a minute here, okay?
{DIALOGUE}: You're telling me it can imitate anything it touches?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: Anything it samples by physical contact.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John thinks about that, trying to grasp their opponent's parameters.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Like it could disguise itself as anything... a pack of cigarettes?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: No.
{DIALOGUE}: Only an object of equal size.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John's still reeling from meeting one terminator, which now seems downright conventional next to the exotic new model.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Well, why doesn't become a bomb or something to get me?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: It can't form complex machines.
{DIALOGUE}: Guns and explosives have chemicals, moving parts.
{DIALOGUE}: It doesn't work that way.
{DIALOGUE}: But it can form solid metal shapes.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 56 INT. VOIGHT HOUSE - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: T-1000 walks down the dark hall.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It passes the bathroom and we see the real Janelle's legs through the half-open door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The shower is running.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her blood mixes with water on the white tile floor.
{META_DATA}: 56A In John's bedroom the T-1000 begins searching methodically in the
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: dark.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Calmly and dispassionately ripping the room apart for any clues that could lead it to its target.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: T-1000 finds a box of audio cassettes marked "Messages from Mom".
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In it are some letters, and envelopes filled with snapshots.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It begins looking through some of the photos...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SHOT OF JOHN AND SARAH during the missing years.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah in olive cammos with an RPG 7 grenade launcher, teaching John how to aim.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah with a group of military-clad Guatemalan men, standing next to cases of Stinger missiles.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John and Sarah in a Contra camp, deep in the mountains.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 57 EXT. PARKING LOT - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John is now sitting on the curb, lost in stunned thought.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator stands above him, watching the street like a Doberman.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He glances down at John.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: We spent a lot of time in Nicaragua... places like that.
{DIALOGUE}: For a while she was with this crazy ex-Green Beret guy, running guns.
{DIALOGUE}: Then there were some other guys.
{DIALOGUE}: She'd shack up with anybody she could learn from.
{DIALOGUE}: So then she could teach me how to be this great military leader.
{DIALOGUE}: Then she gets busted and it's like... sorry kid, your mom's a psycho.
{DIALOGUE}: Didn't you know?
{DIALOGUE}: It's like... everything I'd been brought up to believe was just made-up fantasy, right?
{DIALOGUE}: I hated her for that.
{META_DATA}: (he looks up)
{DIALOGUE}: But everything she said was true.
{META_DATA}: (he stands)
{DIALOGUE}: We gotta get her out of there.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: Negative.
{DIALOGUE}: The T-1000's highest probability for success now would be to copy Sarah Connor and wait for you to make contact with her.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Oh, great.
{DIALOGUE}: And what happens to her?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator's reply is matter-of-fact.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: Typically, the subject being copied is terminated.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: TERMINATED!?
{DIALOGUE}: Shit!
{DIALOGUE}: Why didn't you tell me?
{DIALOGUE}: We gotta right now!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: Negative.
{DIALOGUE}: She is not a mission priority.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Yeah, well fuck you, she's a priority to me!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John strides away.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator goes after him and grabs him arm.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John struggles against the grip.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Which doesn't do him much good.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Hey, goddammit!
{DIALOGUE}: What's your problem?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Starts dragging John back to the bike.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John spots a couple of collage-age slab-o-meat JOCK-TYPES across the street and starts yelling to them.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Help!
{DIALOGUE}: HELP!!
{DIALOGUE}: I'm being kidnapped!
{DIALOGUE}: Get this psycho off of me!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The TWO JOCKS start toward him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John yells in outrage to Terminator.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Let go of me!!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: To his surprise, Terminator's hand opens so fast John falls right on his butt.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks up at the open hand.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Oww!
{DIALOGUE}: Why'd you do that?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: You told me to.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John stares at him in amazement as he realizes...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: You have to do what I say?!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: That is one of my mission parameters.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Prove it... stand on one foot.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator expressionlessly lifts one leg.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John grins.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He's the first on his block...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Cool!
{DIALOGUE}: My own terminator.
{DIALOGUE}: This is great!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The two guys get there and look at Terminator standing there calmly with one leg up in the air.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: This big guy in black leather and dark glasses, standing like a statue.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FIRST JOCK
{DIALOGUE}: Hey, kid.
{DIALOGUE}: You okay?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John turns to him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: No longer needing to be rescued.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Take a hike, bozo.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: FIRST JOCK
{DIALOGUE}: Yeah?
{DIALOGUE}: Fuck you, you little dipshit.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Dipshit?
{DIALOGUE}: Did you say dipshit?!
{META_DATA}: (to Terminator)
{DIALOGUE}: Grab this guy.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator complies instantly, hoisting him one-handed by the collar.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: the guy's legs are pinwheeling.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Now who's the dipshit, you jock douchebag?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Immediately, things get out of hand.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The guy's friend jumps behind Terminator and tries to grab him in a full nelson -- Terminator throws the first guy across the hood of a car -- Grabs the second by the hair, whips out his .45 in a quick blur, and aims the muzzle at the guy's forehead.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John grabs Terminator's arm with a yell as he pulls the trigger -- John's weight is just enough to deflect the gun a few inches.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The guy flinches, stunned by the K-BOOM next to his ear.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He stares, shocked.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Pissing himself.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John is freaking out, too.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He screams at Terminator.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Put the gun down!
{DIALOGUE}: NOW!!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator sets the .45 on the sidewalk.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John scoops it up fast then turns to the shocked civilians, who can't believe what just happened.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Walk away.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They do.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Fast.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John grabs Terminator by the arm and tugs him toward the bike.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John still holds the gun, reluctant to give it back.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Jesus... you were gonna kill that guy!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: Of course.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm a terminator.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John stares at him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Having your own terminator just became a little bit less fun to him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Listen to me, very carefully, okay?
{DIALOGUE}: You're not a terminator any more.
{DIALOGUE}: Alright?
{DIALOGUE}: You got that?
{DIALOGUE}: You can't just go around killing people!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: Why?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Whattaya mean, why?
{DIALOGUE}: 'Cause you can't!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: Why?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: You just can't, okay?
{DIALOGUE}: Trust me on this.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator doesn't get it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John just stares at him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Frightened at what just almost happened.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He gets a glimpse of the responsibility that comes with power.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Finally he hands the .45 back to Terminator, who puts it away.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Look, I'm gonna go get my mom.
{DIALOGUE}: You wanna come along, that's fine with me.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 58 INT. VOIGHT HOUSE/BEDROOM - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: T-1000 finds an envelope... a letter from Sarah to John sent since she's been at Pescadero State Hospital.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It reads the return address on the envelope.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It has what it needs.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It picks up a tape player and the battered shoebox full of Sarah's tapes and exits.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{META_DATA}: 59 CLOSE ON A BLACK & WHITE PHOTOGRAPH. The image is a nightmare from
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: the past.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It is a surveillance camera still-frame from the L.A. police station where the first terminator made such an impression in 1984.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We see the blurry forms of the cop frozen in the emergency lights of a burning corridor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A black-clad figure stands at the end of the corridor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The guy has short-cropped hair and dark glasses.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: An AR-80 assault rifle in one hand, and a 12-gauge in the other -- holding them both like toy pistols.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ANOTHER PHOTO is slapped on top of the first.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Another still-frame blow-up is placed over the last.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator looms in CLOSEUP.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DETECTIVE WEATHERSBY (O.S.)
{DIALOGUE}: These were taken at the West Highland police station in 1984.
{DIALOGUE}: You were there.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WIDER.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We're in --
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 59A INT. INTERVIEW ROOM/PESCADERO - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The photos are lying on the table in front of Sarah, placed there by DETECTIVE WEATHERSBY.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His partner DET. MOSSBERG, and Dr. Silberman, sit at the table as well.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Two uniformed cops, plus Douglas, stand by the door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah stares listlessly at the top photo.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She's withdrawn, haggard... drugged-looking.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MOSSBERG
{DIALOGUE}: He killed seventeen police officers that night.
{DIALOGUE}: Recognize him?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Weathersby slaps another black-and-white eight-by-ten on the table.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A closeup of Terminator taken by the Japanese tourist at the mall.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's the same face.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MOSSBERG
{DIALOGUE}: This one was taken by a Japanese tourist today.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah doesn't react.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's hard to tell she's thinking.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Whether she's up hope or is just in a drugged stupor.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: WEATHERSBY
{DIALOGUE}: Ms. Connor, you've been told that your son's missing.
{DIALOGUE}: His foster parents have been murdered, and we know this guy's involved.
{DIALOGUE}: Talk to us.
{DIALOGUE}: Don't you care?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah stares up at him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A cold and empty stare.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He glances at Silberman.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then at his partner.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MOSSBERG
{DIALOGUE}: We're wasting out time.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: One of the uniformed cops opens the door and Mossberg strides into the hall.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Weathersby and the two uniforms follow him out, with Silberman right behind.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SILBERMAN
{DIALOGUE}: Sorry, gentleman...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TIGHT ON SARAH, slumped under the bright lights.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Totally out of it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then we see her hand, creeping along the edge of the table toward the stack of photos.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She slips off the paper clip binding the stills together, and hides it between her fingers.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Douglas jerks her up by the arms and leads her out.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 60 INT. SARAH'S CELL
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Douglas inches up the last of Sarah's restraints.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then her leans over her... looking down.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Even wrecked as she is, we see the beauty in her face.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He bends down.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We think he's going to kiss her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Instead he runs his tongue across her face like a dog would.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She seems not to even see him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her dull eyes past him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He can't provoke a reaction.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Even here, strapped down, the two of them alone, she give him no superiority.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He smirks and leaves.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We hear the sound of his night-stick tapping its way down the corridor, growing fainter.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah's eyes snap suddenly alert.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There is intensity and resolve in them.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She slips the paper clip out from between her fingers and awkwardly spreads it open into a straight piece of wire.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: With slow, painful concentration she moves it toward the lock of the restraints that bind her wrists to the bed at her sides.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 61 EXT. ROAD - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator and John charge through the night on the Harley.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Streetlights flare past them like comets.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Two serious guys with a mission.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: One a ten-year old kid, the other a half-man/half-machine cyborg from the post-Apocalyptic future.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 62 INT. SARAH'S CELL
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TIGHT ON RESTRAINT LOCK as it unlatches... successfully picked by Sarah's paper clip.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: This is not an easy thing to do.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: But Sarah taught herself a lot of things in her years of hiding.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SARAH, her hands free, sits up and releases the Velcro straps on her feet.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She rolls off the bed and we see her in a whole new light.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She is totally alert, almost feral in her movements.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 63 EXT. HOSPITAL ENTRANCE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: GUARD SHACK.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A bored security guard glances up as an LAPD black-and- white pulls up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He raises the barricade and nods at the T-1000/cop as it passes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THE CRUISER pulls in next to the other police vehicles.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The T-1000 walks toward the main entrance.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 64 INT. SARAH'S CELL/CORRIDOR
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah is using the paper clip on the door lock.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She hears an echoing tapping sound.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's getting louder, coming her way.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She goes back to work on the lock.
{META_DATA}: 65 IN THE CORRIDOR. Douglas the attendant is tapping his stick along
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: the wall like he does every night on his rounds.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He shines a little mag-light in the windows of the cells as he passes, barely slowing.
{META_DATA}: 65A He rounds the corner. His footsteps echo in the dark hallway.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The tip of the stick hits the wall.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Tap, tap, tap... getting closer to Sarah's cell.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He stops at the door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He is about to shine his light in when he notices that a utility closet across the hall is open.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He goes to shut it, absently flicking his light into the dark closet.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He notices something strange among the buckets and cleaning supplies.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A mop lies on the floor, with its handle snapped off about halfway up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The other half is missing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Douglas ponders this for half a second, then hears a SOUND behind him and spins around.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The sound he heard was Sarah's cell door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The missing two feet of MOP HANDLE fill his vision as it CRACKS viciously across the bridge of his nose.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 250 pounds of doughy attendant hit the floor like a sack of cement.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah slams the makeshift baton down expertly across the back of his head, bouncing him off the linoleum.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lights out, Douglas.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She drags him into her cell and locks him in with his own keys.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then swaps her mop-handle for his nice heavy night-stick.
{META_DATA}: 65B Sarah moves down the dark corridor, cat-stepping in her bare feet.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She holds the baton like a pro, laid back along the forearm, police- style.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She looks dangerous.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 66 INT. HOSPITAL ENTRANCE/CORRIDOR
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A long corridor ends at a reception area, which is closed, and a NIGHT RECEIVING DESK, which is a glass window where they can buzz you in through a heavy door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A NIGHT NURSE types at a desk nearby.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She looks up at the sound of footsteps and sees a young cop (T-1000) walking toward her.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: T-1000
{DIALOGUE}: You have a Sarah Connor here?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She assumes he's with the other cops.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Smiles.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: NIGHT NURSE
{DIALOGUE}: Running late, aren't you?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She turns to the inner door to buzz him in and sees Silberman and the cops coming toward the door from the other side.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: NIGHT NURSE
{DIALOGUE}: Your friends are on their way out now...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: When she turns back to the window, T-1000's no longer there.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She goes to the counter and leans out to see if he's at the drinking fountain or someplace.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: No.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reception is empty.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And so is the long corridor beyond.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She frowns.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Too weird.
{META_DATA}: 66A Silberman comes through the solenoid door with Mossberg and
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Weathersby, the two uniformed cops, and the hospital security guard.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The guard retrieves his 9mm pistol from a lock-out box behind the night desk.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Silberman faces him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SILBERMAN
{DIALOGUE}: Lewis, see these gentleman out and them lock up for the night.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The security guard nods.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Silberman goes back into the secure area of the hospital and the cops walk down the long corridor to the main doors.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: No sign of T-1000.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Mossberg and the other cops exit, and the guard locks the door behind them.
{META_DATA}: 66B The guard walks slowly back along the long corridor. The hall is
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: dark, with the light at the night desk far ahead like a sanctuary.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His footsteps ring hollowly on the tile floor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His keys jingle.
{META_DATA}: 66C ANGLE ON FLOOR as the guard's feet pass through FRAME. An instant
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: later the floor starts to move.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It shivers and bulges upward like a liquid mass, still retaining the two-tone checkerboard of the tile.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It hunches up silently into a quivering shadow in the darkness past the guard.
{META_DATA}: 66D Up ahead we hear typing. The night nurse has her back to us, working.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The guard stops as the drinking fountain.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bends to take a sip.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Behind him the fluid mass as reaches six feet of height and begins to resolve rapidly into a human figure.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It loses the color and texture of the tile and becomes... THE GUARD.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: T-1000's mass has been spread out a quarter of an inch thick over several square yards of floor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The guard walked over the T-1000, and his structure was sampled that instant.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Now we see it drawing in and pulling up to form the figure of the guard.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The T-1000/Guard's feet are the last to form, the last of the "liquid floor" pulling in to form shiny black guard shoes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The shoes detach with a faint sucking sound from the real floor as the T-1000/Guard takes its first step.
{META_DATA}: 66E The real guard spins at the sound of footsteps to see... himself.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He has one deeply disturbing moment to consider the ramifications of that.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then he sees his double calmly raise its hand and, inexplicably, points his right index finger directly at the real guard's face, about a foot away.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In a split second, the finger spears out, elongating into a thin steel rod which snaps out like a stiletto, slamming into the guard's eye.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It punches into the corner of the eye, past the eyeball like a trans- orbital lobotomy tool, and emerges from the back of the guard's skull.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Life quietly empties from the guard's face.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He is dead weight, hanging from the rod/finger with suddenly reacts -- SSSNICK.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As the guard slumps, the T-1000 takes his weight easily with one hand and walks him, like it's carrying a suit on a hanger, back toward the night desk.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The wounds are so tiny, no blood drips onto the floor.
{META_DATA}: 66F ON THE NIGHT NURSE, glancing up as the T-1000/Guard walks past,
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: dragging something casually which she can't see because it's below the countertop.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: NIGHT NURSE
{DIALOGUE}: Whatcha got, Lewis?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: T-1000/GUARD
{DIALOGUE}: Just some trash.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She nods, uninterested.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Keeps typing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: T-1000 moves past, dragging the unseen guard toward a closet down the hall from the night receiving station.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: T-1000/Guard removes the Browning High-Power pistol and the keys from the real guard's belt, then stuffs the body into the utility closet.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 66G INT. CORRIDOR/NIGHT RECEIVING DESK
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: T-1000/Guard comes back out and glances at the nurse.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: T-1000/GUARD
{DIALOGUE}: All set.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She glances toward it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sees the Beretta in its holster.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: NIGHT NURSE
{DIALOGUE}: Gotta check the gun first, Lewis.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: T-1000/GUARD
{DIALOGUE}: Yeah, sorry.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: T-1000 opens the locker and blocks it from her view with its body as it mimes putting the gun in.
{META_DATA}: 66H CLOSE ANGLE ON T-1000'S CHEST, from inside the locker. Instead of
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: setting the gun in the locker, it inserts the pistol into it own chest, where is disappears inside like it was dropped into a pot of hot fudge.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It withdraws its hand.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The chest is once again a surface that looks like cloth, buttons, name-tag etc.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: You'd ever guess it was really an intelligent liquid metal.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: T-1000 slams the locker door and waits as the nurse hits the button unlocking the door with a BUZZ-CLACK.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: T-1000/Guard goes through.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 67 INT. ISOLATION SECURITY CHECKPOINT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A small room before a short SALLY-PORT corridor designed to prevent violent inmates from making a run for it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There are doors at each end.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The first one is barred like a jail-cell door, and the second is a steel fire door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The attendants have a video monitor with which they can see the corridor on the other side of the doors.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The two bored attendants barely notice the T-1000/Guard as it approaches.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Looks briefly at a chart next to the door, seeing SARAH CONNOR is in #19.
{META_DATA}: 67A IN THE ISOLATION WARD, the T-1000 passes a nurses' station which looks
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: a cage, walled in by heavy metal mesh.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Silberman, leaning in the open doorway, is talking to an attendant in the cage.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He doesn't glance twice at Lewis the Guard passing by.
{META_DATA}: 68 SARAH, moving like a ghost in the darkened corridor, hears footsteps
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: coming and quietly but quickly unlocks a cell next to her with Douglas' master key.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 68A She slips into the cell and waits as the footsteps pass.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We glimpse the T-1000/Guard pass the window.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She waits as the footsteps fade away.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She looks over.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A female inmate, strapped to a bed, watches her with bird-like eyes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She puts a finger to her lips -- SSHHH.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The inmate nods.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah exits.
{META_DATA}: 68B POV MOVING TOWARD nurse's station. We hear Silberman's voice,
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: reviewing medication with the night attendant.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ON SILBERMAN, yawning, looking at his watch.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He turns to go... Sarah is there.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She slams into him, hurling him through the door into the cage and follows him in.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The orderly jumps up, going for his stunner, but she nails him with Douglas' baton.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WHAP-WHAP-WHAP!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: You can barely see the thing she's swinging it so fast.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The guys goes down.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Silberman lunges for the alarm button and she cracks down hard on his arm.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He cries out and grabs his wrist.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She grabs him by the hair and slams him face down on the desk, smacking him behind the knees expertly with the baton.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His legs buckle and he drops to his knees with his chin on the desk.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She pins him with one hand.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He face is full of outraged disbelief.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SILBERMAN
{DIALOGUE}: You broke my arm!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: There's 215 bones in the human body, motherfucker.
{DIALOGUE}: That's one.
{DIALOGUE}: Now don't move!
{META_DATA}: 68B Moving rapidly, she whips open a medication drawer and grabs a
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: syringe.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They keep a few of these handy for tranking unruly patients.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She jams it into the orderly's butt and fires the whole shot.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Still holding the empty syringe, she sees what she need next.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They keep the toxic cleaning supplies in here to keep the inmates from drinking Drano.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She grabs a plastic jug of LIQUID PLUM'R and slams it down on the desk inches from Silberman's eyes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She jams the empty syringe into the plastic jug.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Draws back the plunger.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The syringe fills with blue liquid.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She whips it out of the jug and jams the needle into Silberman's neck.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His horrified eyes rack toward it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 10 cc's of blue death fill the cylinder.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her thumb hovers over the plunger.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She jerks him to his feet by the collar and gets a tight grip on him, then hauls him through the door.
{META_DATA}: 69 IN THE CORRIDOR outside cell #19 the T-1000 stops and looks in the
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: window.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Douglas, his face a bloody mess, yells to be heard.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DOUGLAS
{DIALOGUE}: Open the door!
{DIALOGUE}: The goddamn bitch is loose in the halls!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: To Douglas' amazement, Lewis the Guard turns impassively and walks away, leaving him shouting soundlessly at the window.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 70 EXT. HOSPITAL
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator and John are approaching the guard gate on the Harley.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They can see the guard inside looks up at the sound of the engine.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Now remember, you're not gonna kill anyone, right?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: Right.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John looks at him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He's not convinced.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Swear.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: What?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Just say "I swear I won't kill anyone."
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John holds his hand up, like he's being sworn in.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator stares at John a beat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then mimics the gesture.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: I swear I will not kill anyone.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator stops the bike and gets off.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The guard, sensing trouble, has his gun drawn as he comes out of the shack.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator walks toward him drawing his .45 smoothly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BLAM!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He shoots the guard accurately in the thigh.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The guy drops, screaming and clutching his leg.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator kicks the guard's gun away, then smashes the phone in the shack with his fist.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He pushes the button to raise the gate and walks back to the bike.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: He'll live.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator climbs onto the bike.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They drive toward the hospital, heading down an ambulance ramp to an underground receiving area.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 71 INT. ISOLATION FLOOR
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The attendants at the security checkpoint look up at the monitor as someone enters the corridor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They see Sarah, holding Silberman at syringe-point.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah speaks to them through an intercom on the wall.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her voice comes through the speaker.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: Open it or he'll be dead before he hits the floor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The attendants' adrenaline levels just went off the scale.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The first attendant shakes him head no.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The amperage here is really high.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The second attendant keys the intercom switch.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: 2ND ATTENDANT
{DIALOGUE}: There's no way, Connor.
{DIALOGUE}: Let him go.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Silberman's face is the color of suet.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SILBERMAN
{DIALOGUE}: It won't work, Sarah.
{DIALOGUE}: You're no killer.
{DIALOGUE}: I don't believe you'd do it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her voice is a deadly cold hiss.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: You're already dead, Silberman.
{DIALOGUE}: Everybody here dies.
{DIALOGUE}: You know I believe that.
{DIALOGUE}: So don't fuck with me!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SILBERMAN
{DIALOGUE}: Open the goddamn door!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The attendants looks at one another.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: One of them hits the solenoid button.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The far door unlocks.
{META_DATA}: 71A IN THE LOCKOUT CORRIDOR. Sarah pushes Silberman ahead of her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The nearer, barred door must be unlocked manually.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: One of the attendants cautiously approaches.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Nervously unlocks it.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: Step back!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He does.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She faces both of them.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: Down on the floor!
{DIALOGUE}: Now!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They comply.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She comes through with Silberman, giving them a wide berth.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Starts backing down the hall away from them, still holding her hostage.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She's actually pulling this off.
{META_DATA}: 71B ANGLE FROM BEHIND HER. What we can see, but she can't see, it a
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: third orderly waiting just around the corner.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He's poised, ready to jump her when she comes abreast of him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ON SARAH backing up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She reaches the corner.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The third attendant lunges, grabbing her syringe-hand.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah spins on the orderly and catches him across the throat with the nightstick.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He loses interest fast, dropping to his knees and gagging.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Silberman pulls away, screaming at the top of his lungs
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SILBERMAN
{DIALOGUE}: Get her!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They scramble up as Sarah takes off like a shot around the corner.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: One of them hits the panic button and ALARMS begin to sound.
{META_DATA}: 72 IN THE ISOLATION WARD, the T-1000 is looking in at a very stoned
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: attendant inside the nurses' station when the alarms shriek through the halls.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It reaches into its chest and pulls out the 9mm pistol.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Heads for the security entrance.
{META_DATA}: 73 IN ANOTHER CORRIDOR in the maze of the vast hospital, Sarah flies
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: past us, her bare feet slapping on the cold tiles.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The orderlies charge after her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She's like an animal in a maze.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She turns the corner, glancing off the wall, and sprints on without slowing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She reaches a steel door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Tries it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Locked.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Footsteps like a drum solo behind her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She fumbles with Douglas' keys, breathing hard.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Jams the master in.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The orderlies are bearing down on her at full tilt.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah gets the door open.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dives through.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Slams it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She turns a deadbolt knob just as the first orderly grabs the latch on the other side.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He's too late.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah sees them beyond the window, fumbling with their keys.
{META_DATA}: 73A Sarah is in another sally-port corridor. A jail-cell type barred
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: door is between her and the corridors of the ward beyond.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She sprints to the walls of bars, jams her key into the door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She unlocks and pulls open this door just as she hears the latch of the one she just came through being unlocked.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She flings herself frantically through the barred door as the first orderly comes through behind her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She slams the bars shut.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: CLANG.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her keys are dangling from the lock on the other side from her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The orderly is racing at her, white-lipped with rage.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She reaches back through the bars, turns the key, and purposefully snaps it off in the lock.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: An instant later the big orderly slams against the door, grabbing through the bars for her as she dances back just out of reach.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He lunges against the steel bars, unbelievably pissed off.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah takes off running, looking back at the frustrated orderlies.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They're shouting at each other, unable to fit their keys into the lock -- The broken-off key tip makes it impossible to get their keys in.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Silberman shouts at them.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SILBERMAN
{DIALOGUE}: Go around, goddamnit!
{DIALOGUE}: Go around!!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The orderlies run back the way they came, and along a cross-corridor to another set of doors.
{META_DATA}: 73B ON SARAH as she rounds a corner and sees the elevators ahead.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Now she's home-free.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: At a full-tilt sprint, she's nearly there when the elevator doors part...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TERMINATOR steps out... his head swivels to face her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah reacts, stricken by the image from her worst nightmares.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her eyes go wide as momentum carries her forward.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her bare feet slip on the slick tile.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She slams to the floor, staring up at the leather-clad figure with the shotgun.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She loses all semblance of courage and some of her sanity.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She's not even aware that she is screaming, or what would be screaming if she could get the breath to do it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In slowed-down dream-time, Sarah scrambles back along the floor like a crab, spinning and clawing her way to her feet along the wall.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She runs like the wind, like in her nightmare.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: If she looked back she would have seen John step warily out of the corridor behind Terminator.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John, however, catches a glimpse of the fleeing Sarah and figures out instantly what happened.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Mom!!
{DIALOGUE}: Wait!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah doesn't hear.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She has clicked fully into her own nightmare.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They take off running after Sarah.
{META_DATA}: 73C She is pelting down the long corridor, back the way she came. As she
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: reaches an intersection with a cross-corridor a white-clad figure blurs from that corridor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The orderly hits her in a flying tackle.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She skids across the floor, shrieking and struggling.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The other two orderlies leap into the fray.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: No!
{DIALOGUE}: Help me!
{DIALOGUE}: Goddamnit, it's gonna kill us all!!!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She is shouting, pleading, trying to get them to understand what is coming.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They grab her thrashing arms and legs.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They don't even look where the out-of-control woman is pointing... back along the corridor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They have pinned her to the cold tiles, a ring of faces above her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Silberman leans down to her, holding a syringe with a heavy dose of trank.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah cranes her neck and sees the dark silhouette of Terminator coming up behind them.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It is exactly her nightmare.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She screams in utter hopelessness.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator, holding the shotgun in one hand, reaches down and grabs one of the orderlies with his other hand.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He hurls the 200-pound guys against the far wall of the corridor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SMACK!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He drops to the floor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The other two orderlies react instantly, leaping onto the intruder.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator seems to disappear for a moment under the two big guys.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then there is an explosion of white-clad figures, as the orderlies are flung outward like they stepped on a land mine.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: One crashes through a window of safety glass and is caught before a two-story fall by the outer steel bars.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The other crashes through an office door, splintering it into kindling.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Silberman has jumped to hold Sarah.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He is grabbed by a roll of skin at the back of his neck and lifted like a cat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The doctor feel his feet pedaling above the ground.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks into the expressionless face.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And it hit him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah was right... this guy isn't human.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He feels the fabric of reality crumbling.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then he feels himself flying through the air.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The wall smacks him, then the floor kicks him in the face.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He decides to lie there a second.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah blinks, staring up at the figure looming over her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John kneels next to her.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Mom, are you okay?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She looks from Terminator to John.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Back to Terminator.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Is this a nightmare?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Or has she finally gone truly bad?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Incredibly, Terminator politely reaches his hand down to her, offering to help her up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The last thing she ever expected to see.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: Come with me if you want to live.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The orderlies are stirring.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: It's all right, Mom.
{DIALOGUE}: He's here to help.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah, is a daze, takes the huge hand in her shaking fingers.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator lifts her to her feet.
{META_DATA}: 73D John sees a GUARD standing thirty feet away, on the other side of the
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: walls of bars.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John doesn't know what we know, but he knows something's not right with this guy.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator turns to follow John's gaze.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The T-1000 had its pistol in its hand, at its side.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator pushes John behind him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They start backing up.
{META_DATA}: 73E The T-1000 walks forward, reaching the bars. It doesn't stop.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Its body divides like jello around the bars.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As it squeezes itself through like metal playdough, its surface reforms perfectly on our side.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We see it deform and squeeze through like a viscous paste forced past an obstacle.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Silberman has recovered enough to be sitting up and watching this.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: That faint snapping sound is his mind.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There is a CLANK and we see that the guard's gun has caught against the bars... the only solid object.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The T-1000 turns its wrist and tries again, slipping the gun endwise through the gap.
{META_DATA}: 73F Sarah is agape. Not reacting. It's been a heavy day for her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator grabs John by the seat of his pants and hooks him up onto his back.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John grabs him around the neck.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator raises the shotgun and starts backing up.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: Go!
{DIALOGUE}: Run!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah doesn't need to be told twice.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: T-1000 walks toward them, opening fire with the Browning Hi-Power.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator straight-arms the 12-guage like a pistol and FIRES.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The stunned orderlies flop face down on the floor as the corridor is filled with high-velocity lead.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: One of them, stupidly running for the cross-corridor, gets hit by the T-1000.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator is hammered by several slugs, and the T-1000 is cratered by two buckshots hits.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It staggers, but comes on.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In the craters we see bright mercury before they close and reseal, disappearing in a second.
{META_DATA}: 73G Terminator makes it around the corner and breaks into a run. Ahead,
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah is already at the elevator.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator and John pile in and John slaps the button for "Garage Level".
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The doors start to close.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: T-1000 clears the corner.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator slams John and Sarah back against the side walls as the T-1000 charges at them, rapid firing the Browning.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The rounds hit the steel doors as they close.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: T-1000 keeps pumping them at the closing gap.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 73H Inside, they see the backside of the doors denting with the hits that are punching holes in the other side.
{META_DATA}: 73I The Browning locks open, empty. T-1000 drops it without a glance
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: back.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The doors close.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: K-WHAM!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The T-1000 hits them a split second later.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The elevator hasn't moved yet.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SSWWIKK!
{META_DATA}: 73J A sword-like blade rams through in between the doors, forcing them
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: open.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator jams the shotgun through the widening gap.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Punches the muzzle right INTO T-1000's face -- BOOM!!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 73K We get a glimpse of the T-1000's head blown apart by the blast.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It is hurtled back.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The doors close.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The car descends.
{META_DATA}: 73L ON THE T-1000, outside the elevator. Its head, which is blown apart
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: into two doughy masses lying on the shoulders, reforms quickly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There is no trace of the injury.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It sees the closed door and jams its hands between them, its fingertips becoming pry-bars.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It pulls the doors apart with inhuman strength 73M and LEAPS INTO THE OPEN SHAFT.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It falls two floors and...
{META_DATA}: 74 IN THE ELEVATOR. Out trio hears a loud THUMP on the roof.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator, reloading the shotgun, looks up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah grabs the .45 from his waistband and aims it at the ceiling.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BEAT... Then CLANGG!!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: a swordlike shaft punches through the ceiling and spears down four feet into the elevator car.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It is inches from Sarah's face.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She opens fire, BAM-BAM-BAM -- right through the roof.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lighting-fast the lance withdraws and thrusts down again, slashing Terminator's jacket, and missing John by inches.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator chambers a round and K-BOOM!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: the 12-guage opens a hole in the ceiling.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator rocks out in a fury of firing/cocking/firing as the metal shafts slash down again and again.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah yells in pain as one of them slices open her upper arm.
{META_DATA}: 75 The doors open. Sarah pulls John out as soon as the gap is wide
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: enough.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They emerge into the basement.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We see the Harley parked nearby.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator, in a rearguard action, fires another blast through the ceiling and runs out.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He throws his leg over the Harley, kicks it to life with one powerful stroke and then whips something out of the inner pocket of his jacket.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He throws it to John.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A road flare!?
{META_DATA}: 76 In the elevator, the T-1000 has bashed a hole in the ceiling big
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: enough to... Pour itself through.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A massive blob of mercury extrudes from the opening.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The mass drops through the hole, down out of frame, then comes back up into frame as Officer X.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It seems to need just a second to get its mental act together after doing this king of taffy-pull with itself.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It opens its eyes and sees --
{META_DATA}: 77 TERMINATOR, the shot gun held in his teeth, astride the roaring
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Harley twenty feet away.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator twists the throttle and pops the clutch.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The back tire screams on the concrete.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The front wheel lifts off the ground and the heavy bike launches in a thundering wheelie.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator gets off just before the bike hurtles into the elevator.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The Harley slams the T-1000 square and smashes it right through the back wall of the elevator.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator rolls to his feet.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Johns strikes the flare on the concrete.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Tosses it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator catches the life flare with one hand.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Levels the shotgun with the other.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: With his last round he blows a big hole in the bike's gas tank.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Gas splashes everywhere, covering the struggling T-1000.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator tosses the flare.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: KA-VOOOM!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The explosion knocks Terminator backward off his feet, enveloping him in the fireball.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He gets up, smoking, and runs after John and Sarah toward the exit ramp.
{META_DATA}: 78 AT THE EXIT RAMP. They are partway up when a blue-and-white hospital
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: security car comes screeching down the other way.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Without breaking stride Sarah runs right at the car.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It skids to a shrieking halt.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She's in the guy's face with the .45 in both hands.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: Out of the car!!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The patrol guy is thinking what he can try when BLAM!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: she puts a round through the glass next to his head.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: RIGHT NOW!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The door opens and the guy is coming out with his hands up as Terminator arrives.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The cyborg flings the rent-a-cop out of the way and slides behind the wheel.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah gets John into the back seat and dives into the front passenger seat as --
{META_DATA}: 78A Terminator slams the car into reverse and punches it, lighting up the
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: tires on the slick ramp.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator hands the shotgun over his shoulder to John and tells him to reload.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John pulls some shells from the pocket of his army jacket and starts feeding them in.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator power backward up the ramp, scraping along one wall, barely in control.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Because...
{META_DATA}: 79 The T-1000 is running at them out of the inferno below.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: This guy won't quit.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Shifting from chrome mode to cop-form as it runs.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It sprints up the ramp after the retreating car.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: T-1000 is gaining.
{META_DATA}: 80 Terminator hands Sarah another magazine for the .45. She snatches
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: it, drops the other out, and slaps in the new one.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cocks the slide.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The car backs along the service driveway toward the security gate.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John hands the shot gun back to Terminator.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He leans out the window and takes aim at the pursuer.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The T-1000's face is right in the headlights.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 80A Terminator fires, blowing a hole in its shoulder.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Shiny liquid metal visible in the hole, which then closes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 80B Sarah, half out the passenger window, opens fire.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The car crashes backward through the security barricade.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{META_DATA}: (calmly)
{DIALOGUE}: Hang on.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He cuts the wheel hard.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The car slews into a reverse 180, swapping ends with a screech.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: T-1000 is almost on them.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator punches it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The car accelerates forward.
{META_DATA}: 80C T-1000 leaps. Lands on the trunk.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Its hand is a metal crowbar slammed down through the trunk lid.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Feet dragging on the pavement, it slams its other hand down, punching another metal hook into the trunk lid, pulling itself up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator turns to Sarah.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: Drive.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator heaves himself half out the driver's window.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah slaps her foot down on the throttle and steers from the passenger side.
{META_DATA}: 80D T-1000, fully on the car now, holds on with one hook-hand while it
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: slams the other into the back window, sweeping away the glass and missing John by inches as he ducks.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It draws back for another swing, lunging forward as --
{META_DATA}: 80E Terminator whips the shotgun over the roof of the car.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Fires point-blank.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hits the T-1000's arm just above the "hand" which anchors it to the car.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The 12-guage blows the arm apart, severing the hook-hand.
{META_DATA}: 80F T-1000 tumbles backward off the accelerating car.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John looks out the back window, his eyes wide.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He sees the T-1000 roll to his feet and continue running.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: But he's dropping way behind now.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah has the car floored and the liquid-metal killer won't catch them on foot.
{META_DATA}: 80G John watches, in awe, as the "crowbar hand", stuck into the trunk
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: right in front of him, reverts to the neutral polyalloy... a kind of think mercury.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The gray metal slides off the trunk of the car and falls onto the road to lie there in a quivering blob.
{META_DATA}: 80H The car speeds off into the night.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: REVERSE on the T-1000, walking now, coming right up into closeup, watching the tail lights recede.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It looks down.
