{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He and John climb in.
{META_DATA}: 92A IN THE PICKUP. Terminator has this trick (which you could do too if
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: you had servo-driven steel fingers) where he smashes the cowl around a steering column with one blow from the palm of his hand.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: When it shatters he strips it away with a single move, and then turns the stub of the lock-mechanism with his fingertips.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: This starts the vehicle.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It takes about three seconds.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In fact, he does it so quickly, the truck is running by the time John flips down the sun visor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A set of keys drops out and John catches them.
