{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator gets into the Bronco and turns the ignition key and the engine catches with a roar.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Alriight!!
{DIALOGUE}: My man!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: No problemo.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John grins and does a victorious thumbs up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator imitates the gesture awkwardly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John laughs and makes him get out of the truck, to try the move again.
{META_DATA}: A108 SARAH, across the compound, pauses in her work to watch John and
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator.
{META_DATA}: A109 SARAH'S POV... we don't hear what John and Terminator are saying. It
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: is a soundless pantomime as John is trying to show some other gestures to the cyborg.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Trying to get him to walk more casually.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John walks, then Terminator tries it, then John gestures wildly, talking very fast... explaining the fundamental principles of cool.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They try it again.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Continued ad lib as we hear:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: Watching John with the machine, it was suddenly so clear.
{DIALOGUE}: The Terminator would never stop, it would never leave him... it would always be there.
{DIALOGUE}: And it would never hurt him, never shout at him or get drunk and hit him, or say it couldn't spend time with him because it was too busy.
{DIALOGUE}: And it would die to protect him.
{DIALOGUE}: Of all the would-be fathers who came and went over the years, this thing, this machine, was the only one who measured up.
{DIALOGUE}: In an insane world, it was the sanest choice.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah clenches her jaw and goes grimly back to work... a strong woman made hard and cold by years of hard choices.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO;
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: A110 EXT. ROAD - DAY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A police cruiser is parked off the side of a quiet, empty road on the outskirts of Los Angeles.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A ribbon of traffic moves steadily by on a freeway in the distance.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Nothing stirs around the cruiser except some pump-jacks sucking the earth on the hill behind it.
{META_DATA}: A111 IN THE CRUISER. The T-1000 sits inside. John's notes and letters are
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: spread out on the seat beside it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah's voice speaks from a cassette deck.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John's tapes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her voices mixes with the static filled chatter of the radio that T-1000 monitors for any signs of its targets.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: ... if we are ever separated, and can't make contact, go to Enrique's airstrip.
{DIALOGUE}: I'll rendezvous with you there.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: T-1000 whips around and rewinds the tape, replaying the last section.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It then snaps up the envelope of photos we saw earlier.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ECU on envelope.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We see the postmark: "Charon Mesa, Calif."
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TIGHT ON T-1000 staring at the postmark on the envelope.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It glances up at the sound of crunching gravel.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In the rear-view it sees a BIKE COP pulling onto the shoulder behind it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The big KAWASAKI 1100 idles up next to the T-1000, still seated in the cruiser.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: BIKE COP
{DIALOGUE}: Howdy.
{DIALOGUE}: I saw you pulled over here earlier.
{DIALOGUE}: Everything okay?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: T-1000
{DIALOGUE}: Everything's fine.
{DIALOGUE}: Thanks for checking.
{META_DATA}: (it gets slowly out of the car)
{DIALOGUE}: Since you're here, though, can I talk to you a second...
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: A112 EXT. HIGHWAY - DAY/MINUTES LATER
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The T-1000 thunders along on the Kawasaki 1100, doing about a hundred and twenty.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: PAN WITH IT until it recedes toward the horizon.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: A113 EXT. COMPOUND - DAY (LATE AFTERNOON)
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah sits at the picnic table.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The weapons are cleaned and her work is done.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She hasn't slept in twenty-four hours and she seems to have the weight of the whole world on her shoulder.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She draws her knife from its belt sheath.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Idly starts to carve something on the table top... the letter "N".
{META_DATA}: A114 NOT FAR AWAY, John and Terminator are packing the Bronco for the trip.
{META_DATA}: A115 ON SARAH, AT THE TABLE as she looks up from her carving, thinking.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She watches Salceda's kids playing nearby... wrestling with a mutty dog and loving it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah watches Yolanda walking her toddler by her hands.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Backlit, stylized.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She looks over at John.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Loading guns and supplies.
{META_DATA}: A116 ANGLE ON kids playing.
{META_DATA}: A117 SARAH'S HEAD droops. She closes her eyes.
{META_DATA}: A118 TIGHT ON small children playing. Different ones.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Wider now, to reveal a playground in a park.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Very idyllic.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A dream playground, crowded with laughing children playing on swings, slides, and a jungle gym.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It could be the playground we saw melted and frozen in the post-nuclear desolation of 2029.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: But here the grass is vibrant green and the sun is shining.
{META_DATA}: 118A Sarah, short-haired, looking drab and paramilitary, stands outside the
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: playground.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: An outsider.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her fingers are hooked in a chain-link fence and she is staring through the fence at the young mothers playing with their kids.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A grim-faced harbinger.
{META_DATA}: 118B Some girls play skip-rope. Their sing-song weaves through the random
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: burbling laughter of the kids.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: One of the young mothers walks her two-year-old son by the hands.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She is wearing a pink waitress uniform.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She turns to us, laughing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It is Sarah.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beautiful.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Radiant.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah from another life, uncontaminated by the dark future.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She glances at the strange woman beyond the fence.
{META_DATA}: 118C Grim-faced Sarah presses against the fence. She starts shouting at
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: them in SLOW MOTION.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: No sound comes from her mouth.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She grabs the fence in frustration, shaking it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Screaming soundlessly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Waitress Sarah's smile falls.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then returns as her little boy throws some sand at her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She laughs, turns away, as if the woman at the fence were a shadow, a trick of light.
{META_DATA}: 118D-118F OMITTED
{META_DATA}: 118G THE SKY EXPLODES. The children ignite like match heads. Sarah is
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: burning, screaming silently, everything silent and overexposed.
{META_DATA}: 118H THE BLAST WAVE HITS... devouring the cowering mothers and children.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah's scream merges with the howl of the wind as the shockwave rips into her, blasting her apart and she...
{META_DATA}: 119 Wakes up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: All is quiet and normal.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The children are still playing nearby.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Less than fifteen minutes have gone by.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bathed in sweat, Sarah sits hunched over the table.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Every muscle is shaking.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She is gasping.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah struggles to breathe, running her hand through her hair which is soaked with sweat, She can escape from the hospital, but she can't escape from the madness which haunts her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She looks down at the words she has carved on the table, amid the scrawled hearts and bird-droppings.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They are: "NO FATE."
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Something changes in her eyes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She slams her knife down in the table top, embedding it deeply in the words.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then gets up suddenly and we --
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{META_DATA}: A120 LONG LENS on Sarah walking toward us, striding across the compound
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: with grim purpose.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She carries a small nylon pack and a CAR-15 assault rifle.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her face is an impassive mask.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She has become a terminator.
{META_DATA}: A120A JOHN LOOKS UP from his work in time to see Sarah throw the rifle
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: behind the seat of their stolen pickup, jump in and start it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She slams it in gear.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Salceda walks up to John.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SALCEDA
{DIALOGUE}: She said you go south with him...
{META_DATA}: (he points at Terminator)
{DIALOGUE}: ... tonight, like you planned.
{DIALOGUE}: She will meet you tomorrow in...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: But John is moving, running after her.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Mommm!!
{DIALOGUE}: Wait!!
{META_DATA}: A120B MOVING WITH SARAH as she leaves the compound. We see John running
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: after her... yelling.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Can't hear his words.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She looks in the rear- view mirror but doesn't slow down.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: A121 EXT. COMPOUND - DUSK/MINUTES LATER
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John and Terminator ponders the message carved into the top of the picnic table.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah's knife is still embedded there.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: "No fate."
{DIALOGUE}: No fate but what we make.
{DIALOGUE}: My father told her this... I mean I made him memorize it, up in the future, as a message to her -- Never mind.
{DIALOGUE}: Okay, the whole thing goes "The future is not set.
{DIALOGUE}: There is no fate but what we make for ourselves."
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: She intends to change the future somehow.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: I guess, yeah --
{META_DATA}: (snaps his fingers as it hit him)
{DIALOGUE}: Oh shit!!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: Dyson.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Yeah, gotta be!
{DIALOGUE}: Miles Dyson!
{DIALOGUE}: She's gonna blow him away!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John motions to Terminator and breaks into a run.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Come on.
{DIALOGUE}: Let's go.
{DIALOGUE}: LET'S GO!!
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: A122 INT./EXT. SARAH'S JEEP - DUSK
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah speeds through the darkening desert.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Expressionless.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In her dark glasses, she looks as pitiless as an insect.
{META_DATA}: DISSOLVE TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: A123 EXT. HIGHWAY - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TRACKING WITH THE BRONCO, Terminator and John heading toward L.A.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: This is tactically dangerous.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Drive faster.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: The T-1000 has the same files that I do.
{DIALOGUE}: It could anticipate this move and reacquire you at Dyson's house.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: I don't care.
{DIALOGUE}: We've gotta stop her.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: Killing Dyson might actually prevent the war.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: I don't care!!
{DIALOGUE}: There's gotta be another way.
{DIALOGUE}: Haven't you learned anything?!
{DIALOGUE}: Haven't you figured out why you can't kill people?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator is still stumped.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Look, maybe you don't care if you live or die.
{DIALOGUE}: But everybody's not like that!
{DIALOGUE}: Okay?!
{DIALOGUE}: We have feelings.
{DIALOGUE}: We hurt.
{DIALOGUE}: We're afraid.
{DIALOGUE}: You gotta learn this stuff, man, I'm not kidding.
{DIALOGUE}: It's important.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: PANNING as they pass, revealing the lights of the city ahead.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{META_DATA}: A124 EXT, DYSON'S HOUSE - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The house is high-tech and luxurious.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Lots of glass.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dyson's study is lit bluish with the glow of his computer monitors.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He is at the terminal, working.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Where else?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We see him clearly in a long shot from an embankment behind the house.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A DARK FIGURE moves into the foreground.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Rack focus to Sarah as she turns into profile.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She raises the CAR-15 rifle and begins screwing the long heavy cylinder of a sound-suppresser onto the end of the barrel.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{META_DATA}: A125-A125K OMITTED
{META_DATA}: 129 OMITTED
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 129A INT. DYSON HOUSE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dyson's kids, Danny and Blythe, are playing in the halls with a radio- controlled off-road truck.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Danny drives and Blythe scampers after it, trying to catch it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They stop in the hall outside Dyson's study and sees him working at his terminal.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Danny puts a finger to his lips, shushing Blythe.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His expression is mischievous.
{META_DATA}: 129B With the silencer in place, Sarah eases back the bolt and then slips
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: it forward, chambering a .223 round.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then she lies down on the embankment.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He cheek pressed against the cool rifle-stock, she slides one hand slowly forward to brace the weapon, taking the weight on her elbow.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her other hand slips knowingly to the trigger.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her expression is cold, impassive.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She looks through the scope at the man in the house.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She feels nothing as she raises the rifle.
{META_DATA}: 130 OMITTED
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 130A INT. DYSON'S HOUSE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: DYSON, in deep thought.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The rhythmic sounds of keys as he works.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Symbols on the screen shift.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ON HIS BACK we see the glowing red dot appear.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It is the target dot of Sarah's laser designator.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It moves silently up his back toward his head.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 131 EXT. DYSON HOUSE/EMBANKMENT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IN EXTREME CLOSEUP we see Sarah's eye at the night-scope.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TIGHT INSERT on her finger as it tightens on the trigger, taking out the slack.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She takes a deep breath and holds it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Adjusts her position minutely.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 132 INT. DYSON HOUSE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The laser dot jiggles on the back of Dyson's neck and then rises, centering on the back of his skull.
{META_DATA}: 132A LOW ANGLE as Danny's Bigfoot truck roars toward us -- FILLING FRAME.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Thump.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It hits Dyson's foot.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He jerks, startled, and looks down as -- POP!!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 132B His monitor screen is BLOWN OUT spraying his with glass.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He jerks back, utterly shocked... and spins to see the huge hole blown through the window behind him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: This saves him as K-THUMP!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: -- the second shot blows the top of his high-backed chain into an explosion of stuffing an inch from his head.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Instinctively he dives to the carpet as --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BLAM BLAM BLAM -- rounds blast through the window, tearing into his desk and computer, blowing his keyboard into shrapnel.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 132C With the monitor screen blown out, the room is in darkness.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah can't see Dyson now, down behind his desk.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She puts round after round into the heavy desk, blasting one side of it into kindling.
{META_DATA}: 132D Dyson, scared out of his mind, has his face jammed against the carpet,
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: terrified to move.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He sees his kids in the hall.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DYSON
{DIALOGUE}: Run, kids!
{DIALOGUE}: Go!
{DIALOGUE}: Run!
{META_DATA}: 132E IN THE HALL, TARISSA rounds the corner at a dead run. She sees the
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: kids running toward her and grabs them in her arms.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Down the hall, in the dark study, she sees Dyson on the floor amid the splinters and shrapnel of the continuing fusillade.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TARISSA
{DIALOGUE}: Miles!
{DIALOGUE}: Oh my God!!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: MILES
{DIALOGUE}: Stay back!!
{META_DATA}: 132F ON THE FLOOR, Dyson flinches as chucks of wood and shattered computer
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: components shower down on him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks desperately toward the door, but knows he'd be totally exposed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He'd never make it.
{META_DATA}: 133 SARAH's rifle empties with a final CLACK!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She throws it down and draws her .45 smoothly from a shoulder base.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She starts toward the house, snapping back the slide on the pistol, chambering a round.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She is in a fast, purposeful walk, keeping her eyes fixed on the target.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She is utterly determined to kill this man.
{META_DATA}: 134 FROM UNDER THE DESK Dyson can see a sliver in the backyard. He sees
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah's feet as she strides toward him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He tenses to make a break for the door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah raises the pistol, eyes riveted ahead, controlling her breathing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dyson springs up in a full-tilt sprint.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She tracks him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He hooks a foot on the cord of a toppled disk drive.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BOOM!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her shot blows apart a lamp where his head was.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He hits the floor hard, but keeps moving, scrambling forward.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Crunch of glass behind his as Sarah's dark form is framed in the blown-out floor-to-ceiling window.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dyson leaps toward the hall.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BOOM!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her second shot spins him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He hits the floor in the hallway.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Tarissa is screaming.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dyson struggles forward, stunned.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There is a .45-caliber hole clean through his left shoulder.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He smears the wall with blood as he staggers up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Looking back, he sees the implacable figure behind him, coming on.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He topples through a doorway as -- BOOM!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BOOM!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Shots blowing away the molding where he just was.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 135 EXT. DYSON HOUSE/STREET
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator and John leap from the jeep, sprinting toward the house.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The shots sound muffles from outside.
