{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The black gun muzzle is a foot from his face.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DYSON
{META_DATA}: (gasping)
{DIALOGUE}: Please... let... the kids... go...
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: Shut up!
{DIALOGUE}: SHUT UP!!
{DIALOGUE}: Motherfucker!
{DIALOGUE}: It's all your fault!
{DIALOGUE}: IT'S YOUR FAULT!!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We see her psyching herself to pull the trigger... needing now to hate this man she doesn't know.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's a lot harder face-to-face.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She is bathed in sweat, and it runs into her eyes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Blinking, she wipes it fast with one hand, then gets it back on the gun.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The .45 is trembling.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TIGHT ON SARAH as we see the forces at war behind her eyes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She looks into the faces of Dyson, Tarissa, Blythe, Danny.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah takes a sharp breath and all the muscles in her arms contract as she tenses to fire.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: But her finger won't do it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She lowers the gun very slowly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It drops to her side in one hand.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: All the breath and energy seems to go out of her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She weakly raises her other hand in a strange gesture, like "Stay where you are, don't move".
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As if, should they move, the fragile balance might tip back the other way.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She backs away from them slowly, panting.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's as if she's backing away in terror from what she almost did.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She reaches a wall and slumps against it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Slides down to her knees.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The gun falls limply from her fingers.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She rests her cheek against the wall.
{META_DATA}: 136A The front door is kicked in.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator steps inside.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John grabs his sleeve and pushes past him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He scopes out the situation in two seconds... Sarah, the gun, the sobbing family.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John moves to Sarah while Terminator checks Dyson.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John kneels in front of his mother.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She raises her head to look at him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He sees the tears spilling down her cheeks,
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Mom?
{DIALOGUE}: You okay?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: I couldn't... oh, God.
{META_DATA}: (she seems to she him for the first time)
{DIALOGUE}: You... came here... to stop me?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Uh huh.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She reaches out and takes his shoulder suddenly, surprising him... drawing him to her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She hugs him and a great sob wells up deep inside her, from a spring she had thought long dry.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She hugs him fiercely as the sobs wrack her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John clutches her shoulders.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It is all he ever wanted.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: It's okay.
{DIALOGUE}: It'll by okay.
{DIALOGUE}: We'll figure it out.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: I love you, John.
{DIALOGUE}: I always have.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: I know, Mom.
{DIALOGUE}: I know.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TARISSA looks around at the bizarre tableau.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator has wordlessly ripped open Dyson's shirt and examined the wound.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: Clean penetration.
{DIALOGUE}: No shattered bone.
{DIALOGUE}: Compression should control the loss of blood.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He takes Tarissa's hands and presses them firmly over the entrance and exit wounds.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: Do you have bandages?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DYSON
{DIALOGUE}: In the bathroom.
{DIALOGUE}: Danny, can you get them for us?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Danny nods and runs down the hall.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John disengages from Sarah.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She wipes her tears, the instinct to toughen up taking over again.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: But the healing moment has had its effect, nevertheless.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John walks toward Dyson and Terminator.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DYSON
{DIALOGUE}: Who are you people?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John draws the Biker's knife from Terminator's boot.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hands it to him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Show him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator takes off his jacket to reveal bare arms.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John takes Blythe by the hands and leads her down the hall, away from what is about to happen.
{META_DATA}: 136B TIGHT ON TERMINATOR'S left forearm as the knife makes a deep cut just
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: below the elbow.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In one smooth motion, Terminator cuts all the way around his arm.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: With a second cut, he splits the skin of the forearm from elbow to wrist.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TERMINATOR grasps the skin and strips is off his forearm like a surgeon rips off a rubber glove.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It comes off with a sucking rip, leaving a bloody skeleton.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: But the skeleton is made of bright metal, and is laced with hydraulic actuators.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The fingers are as finely crafted as watch parts... they flex into a fist and extend.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator holds it up, palm out, in almost the exact position of the one in the vault at Cyberdyne,
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: HOLD ON DYSON reacting to the servo-hand in front of him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He's seen one of these before.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Tarissa is screaming now, but he doesn't hear her.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DYSON
{DIALOGUE}: My God.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: Now listen to me very carefully.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 137 INT. HOUSE/KITCHEN - LATER
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah puts out her fifth cigarette.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She's sitting on the counter.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John, Terminator, Dyson, and Tarissa are at the kitchen table, under a single overhead light.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dyson looks like that guy on the Sistine Chapel wall, the damned soul... eyes fixed and staring with terrifying knowledge.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His shoulder is bandaged.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator's arm is wrapped with a blood-soaked bandage below the elbow.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The steel forearm and hand gleam in the harsh kitchen light.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TRACKING AROUND THE TABLE as Terminator speaks... we don't hear the words.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: Dyson listened while the Terminator laid it all down.
{DIALOGUE}: Skynet.
{DIALOGUE}: Judgment Day... the history of things to come.
{DIALOGUE}: It's not every day you find out you're responsible for 3 billion deaths.
{DIALOGUE}: He took it pretty well, considering...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator finishes speaking.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DYSON
{DIALOGUE}: I feel like I'M gonna throw up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks around at them, clutching the table like he's about to blow away.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His face, his posture, his ragged voice express soul-wrenching terror.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: This is a man ripped out of normal life into their grim world.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His voice is pleading.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DYSON
{DIALOGUE}: You're judging me on thing's I haven't even done yet.
{DIALOGUE}: Jesus.
{DIALOGUE}: How were we supposed to know?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah speaks from the shadows behind them.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dyson turns to find her looking right at him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: Yeah.
{DIALOGUE}: Right.
{DIALOGUE}: How were you supposed to know?
{DIALOGUE}: Fucking men... all you know how to do is thrust into the world with your... fucking ideas and your weapons.
{DIALOGUE}: Did you know that every gun in the world is named after a man?
{DIALOGUE}: Colt, Browning, Smith, Thompson, Kalashnikov... all men.
{DIALOGUE}: Men built the hydrogen bomb, not women... men like you thought it up.
{DIALOGUE}: You're so creative.
{DIALOGUE}: You don't know what it's like to really create something... to create a life.
{DIALOGUE}: To feel it growing inside you.
{DIALOGUE}: All you know how to create is death... you fucking bastards.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Mom, Mom, we need to be more constructive here.
{DIALOGUE}: I don't see this as a gender-related issue.
{META_DATA}: (to the Dysons)
{DIALOGUE}: She's still tense.
{META_DATA}: (to Sarah)
{DIALOGUE}: We still have to figure out how to stop it all from happening.
{DIALOGUE}: Right?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TARISSA
{DIALOGUE}: But I thought... aren't we changing things?
{DIALOGUE}: I mean... right now?
{DIALOGUE}: Changing the way it goes?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DYSON
{META_DATA}: (seizing on that)
{DIALOGUE}: That's right!
{DIALOGUE}: There's no way I'm going to finish the new processor now.
{DIALOGUE}: Forget it.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm out of it.
{DIALOGUE}: I'm quitting Cyberdyne tomorrow... I'll sell real estate, I don't care,,,
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{META_DATA}: (coldly)
{DIALOGUE}: That's not good enough.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dyson's voice is pitiful.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DYSON
{DIALOGUE}: Look, whatever you want me to do, I'll do.
{DIALOGUE}: I just want my kids to have a chance to grow up, okay?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: No one must follow your work.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DYSON
{META_DATA}: (thoughts racing)
{DIALOGUE}: Alright, yeah.
{DIALOGUE}: You're right.
{DIALOGUE}: We have to destroy the stuff at the lab, the files, disk drive... and everything I have here.
{DIALOGUE}: Everything!
{DIALOGUE}: I don't care.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{META_DATA}: 138 FIRE ROARING IN A METAL TRASH BARREL.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Stacks of files are dumped onto it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WIDER reveals we are in --
{META_DATA}: 138A EXT, DYSON'S BACKYARD - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator dumps lighter fluid liberally over the fire, which flares up, lighting his face demonically.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah, Dyson, Tarissa, and John return from his office with more stuff -- files, notes, optical disks.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Even his kids are carrying stuff.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It all goes into the fire.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dyson drops the prototype onto the fire... his eyes hollow and distant.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He stares into the fire, watching his world burning.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The has a sudden thought.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DYSON
{DIALOGUE}: Do you know about the chip?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: What chip?
