{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: close to the building.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It rakes its XENON SPOTLIGHT through the second floor offices.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 154 INT./EXT. SECOND FLOOR OFFICE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator crosses the office toward the floor-to-ceiling windows.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He is outlines starkly by the spotlight as it rakes through the dark offices.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Without breaking stride he kicks an executive desk toward the window.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 154A Glass explodes outward and the desk topples, falling to the sidewalk below.
{META_DATA}: 154B Terminator, standing at the edge, FIRES A LONG BURST with strafes the
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: police cars lines up below.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cops duck as glass flies.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator, with his superb aim, hits no one.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: But noticed is served.
{META_DATA}: 154C The cops (surprise) FIRE BACK. Terminator turns and is walking
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: calmly from the window as glass, office furniture, drapes etc. are riddled by return fire.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A few rounds hit his back, but he doesn't notice.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He reloads as he walks.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 155 INT. VAULT ANTECHAMBER
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TIGHT ON A KEY inserted into one of the vault locks.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WIDER as John and Dyson stand poised, hands on keys.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: And let's see what's behind door number one.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dyson nods and they turns the keys together.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The vault grumbles to itself, withdrawing it locking bolts with a final KLONK!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Together Dyson and John swing the door open.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 156 EXT./INT. LOBBY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The varsity takes the field as the SWAT TROOPERS sprint forward by squads.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They flank the lobby and work their way inside, deploying rapidly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They move and freeze, behind cover, quivering with adrenaline.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They have all that great SWAT equipment: body armor, gas-masks, M-16s, tear-gas launchers, ropes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The works.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They make a lot of hand signals and keep their mouths shut.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They're well- trained and deadly.
{META_DATA}: 157 OUTSIDE we see cops firing TEAR GAS grenades through the broken
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: windows into second-floor offices.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 158 INT. VAULT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John and Dyson are isolated from the world in this silent steel womb.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dyson opens the cabinet containing the terminator relics.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's John turn to stare with uneasy deja-vu as he sees the terminator hand and CPU.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then in one vicious move he sweeps his arm behind the inert-gas flasks and hurls them to the floor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They SHATTER.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John snatches the CPU and the metal hand out of the broken glass.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Got ol' Skynet by the ball now, Miles.
{DIALOGUE}: Come on, let's book!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Clutching the steel hand and pocketing the chip like it's a Mars bar he just bought, John runs out.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dyson follows.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 159 INT. FIRST FLOOR CORRIDOR/STAIRWELL
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We see the advance squad of SWATs make it to one of the stairwells.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They start up, two at a time, covering each other ritualistically by the numbers.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 160 INT. LAB/HALL
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John pelts into the lab with Dyson stumbling along behind him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah is just finished wiring all the charges to the central detonator.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Ready to rock?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: Ready.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John tosses her the metal hand.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She catches it and bends to put the hand in her empty back-pack.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah zips the pack and starts to shuck into it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dyson's running out of steam.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The bandages at his shoulder are soaked with seeping blood.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He stands in the middle of the lab, saying goodbye in his mind, looking weak and empty.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator strides into the lab.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: Time to go.
{DIALOGUE}: Right now.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He and John head back the way they came, through security.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah sees that in her work, she has set the detonator down twenty feet away, near where Dyson is standing.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: Dyson, hand me the detonator.
{DIALOGUE}: Let's go --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He gingerly picks up the detonator.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Starts toward her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then -- 160A CRASH!!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THE DOORS AT THE BACK END OF THE LAB ARE KICKED OPEN.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SWAT LEADER and two others OPEN FIRE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Their M-16s rake the room.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah dives behind a computer cabinet.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dyson is HIT.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He is slammed to the floor by the impacts.
{META_DATA}: 161 IN THE HALL, John hears the firing and spins to run back.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Mommm!!!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator grabs him as bullets slam into his broad back.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He makes it around the corner with John, out of the line of fire.
{META_DATA}: 162 IN THE LAB, bullets rake over Sarah's head, smacking all around her,
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: clanging into the machine protecting her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She can see Dyson, slumped on the floor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Debris and flying glass rain on her as the SWATs pour on the fire.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The detonator is clutched in his hand.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He rolls to face her, his eyes bulging from the pain of his torn-up guts.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DYSON
{DIALOGUE}: Go.
{META_DATA}: 162A Sarah hesitates a split second. Then she snap-rolls and fast-crawls
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: through broken glass and debris into the hall where --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TERMINATOR grabs her by the jacket and hauls her roughly to her feet.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Bullets rake the walls behind them as they sprint forward.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They round the corner.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John does a fast take that she's not hit and they run together through the security checkpoint.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 163 INT. SECURITY STATION/CORRIDOR
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John reaches the first door, and tries it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Locked.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator unslings the M-79 blooper smoothly, opening the breach.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: Get back.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He pulls a grenade from the bandolier over his shoulder, and slides it into the bore.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Flick his wrist.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The breech snaps shut.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah and John have a split second to duck and cover.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: Cover you ears and open you mouth.
{META_DATA}: 163A They do. KABOOM!!! Twenty feet away the door, and half the wall
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: around it, EXPLODES outward.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The backblast hits Terminator full force, but he strides through the smoking hole before the debris has even hit the floor.
{META_DATA}: 164 OMITTED
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 165 INT. LAB
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SWAT LEADER moves cautiously through the lab.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cat-stepping, he circles around a desk which block Dyson's body from his view.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His M-16 is leveled crisply.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We look over his shoulder as he rounds the desk, revealing --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: MILES DYSON is not dead.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He will be very soon, but at this moment he is conscious.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He has propped himself up against the desk, and holds a BOOK in one hand.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A heavy technical manual.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Below the book is the detonator, upright on the tile floor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The message is clear.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: "Shoot me, the book drops on the plunger.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Adios."
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dyson wheezes, trying to draw enough breath to talk.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DYSON
{DIALOGUE}: I don't know... how much longer... I can... hold this thing...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SWAT Leader seems to see the wires, the claymores, the gas cans all around him for the first time.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His eyes, visible through his gas- mask, go very wide.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He spins and motions his squad back.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: LEADER
{DIALOGUE}: Fall back!!
{DIALOGUE}: Everybody out!
{DIALOGUE}: Move it!
{DIALOGUE}: OUT NOW!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They retreat so fast they crash into the next group coming up the stairs.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 166 INT. CORRIDOR
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator reaches the main elevators.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hits the button.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah and John are coughing and stumbling in the choking darkness, buddy- breathing with the single mask.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The doors open.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They get in the elevator and head down.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 167 INT. LAB
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dyson is lying amid the ruins of his dreams.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sprawled on the floor, he has his back propped up against the desk.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He is bathed in his own blood, which runs out in long fingers across the tiles.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His breathing is shallow and raspy.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He still holds the book, trembling, above the switch.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In his lap is the picture from his desk.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He has pulled it from the debris next to him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A tear trickles from his eye.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His wife and children smile up at him through broken glass.
{META_DATA}: 168 OMITTED
{META_DATA}: 169 CUT TO THE PUPIL OF HIS EYE, at the moment of death, the instant the
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: light fade from his eyes and he is gone -- His arm drops and the book his the switch --
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 170 EXT. BUILDING
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As the face of the building EXPLODES in an eruption of glass and fire.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Remains of the second-floor windows shower the parking lot and a huge fireball rolls out, leaping into the sky.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The cops look up, stunned.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The helicopter banks away from the heat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Burning debris falls among the cop cars and a number of officers break ranks, pulling back.
{META_DATA}: 171 ONLY ONE OF THEM seems to be moving with purpose. A BIKE COP who has
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: just arrived drives through the disorganized crowd, directly toward the building.
{META_DATA}: 171A T-1000 guns the bike up a ramp to a pedestrian bridge which crosses
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: from a parking structure to the Cyberdyne building.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It enters on the second floor, which is now a burning maze.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 172 INT. SECOND FLOOR/OFFICE/CORRIDOR
