{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They're totally trapped, cut off and screwed.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{META_DATA}: (to Sarah)
{DIALOGUE}: Don't forget.
{DIALOGUE}: It's always darkness right before... you're totally fucked.
{META_DATA}: 173A The SWATs fire a tear-gas grenade toward the elevators. It spews the
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: vicious CS gas out in a swirling cloud which envelops Sarah and John, who are pressed against the back wall of the elevator.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: Keep your eyes closed.
{DIALOGUE}: Don't move.
{META_DATA}: (they nod, eyes squeezed shut)
{DIALOGUE}: I'll be back.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He slings the grenade launcher over his shoulder and walks out into the corridor.
{META_DATA}: 173B BLAM. A tear-gas grenade ricochets from wall to wall as it flies down
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: the corridor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It skids to rest in front of Terminator, throwing out a white cloud which quickly fills the corridor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 173C In the elevator, Sarah and John are choking, handing the breathing mask back and forth desperately.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They're scarred.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: This looks like it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 173D ANGLE ON THE SWAT TEAM, gripping their weapons at the mouth of the corridor.
