{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 177 INT./EXT SECOND FLOOR
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: T-1000, astride the Kawasaki, looks down from a second-floor office and sees the van tearing across the parking lot with the remaining cops firing at it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It knows.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It looks around.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Analyzing options.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It sees the helicopter hovering outside the building at the end of this corner office block... It twists full throttle on the powerful bike.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Roars through the office, accelerating fast, straight at the windows --
{META_DATA}: 178 T-1000 BLASTS OUT THROUGH THE GLASS, airborne on the motorcycle. It
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: rockets across the gap to the hovering chopper and -- 178A SLAMS into the canopy.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The impact of bike and rider pitches the chopper radically.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The startled PILOT fights to regain control as the bike tumbles to the pavement below.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 178B The T-1000 doesn't.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It clings to the shattered canopy.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Nightmarishly, the pilot watches as the T-1000 smashes its head through the plexiglass canopy and rapidly POURS ITSELF through the jagged hole.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It reforms instantly into its previous self on the passenger seat.
{META_DATA}: 178C It hurls the pilot out of the chopper and slides into the driver's
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: seat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The chopper is auto-rotating, spinning out of control.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It drops toward the parking lot.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: T-1000 recovers control ten feet above the ground.
{META_DATA}: 178D Cops hits the deck as the tail-boom swings around, going over them by
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: inches.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The chopper lifts out in a power climb, roaring away across the parking lot toward the fleeing SWAT van.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: OKAY, BUCKLE YOUR SEATBELTS, HERE IT COMES...
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 179 INT./EXT. SWAT VAN/HIGHWAY - NIGHT
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator looks back at his two passengers as he turns the boxy van onto a divided highway.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah and John are catching their breath, still coughing from the CS gas.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator look to the rear-view mirror.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He sees the xenon searchlight of the chopper behind them, gaining.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah looks around the inside of the SWAT van.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It is a rolling armory.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There are rifles, ballistic vests, all manner of equipment.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: John, get under these.
{DIALOGUE}: Hurry!
