{META_DATA}: 181D Terminator sees the T-1000 preparing to fire again.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He locks up the van's brakes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Tires scream as the vehicle shimmies.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah is thrown forward, sliding up to the bulkhead next to John.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 182 And the helicopter SLAMS RIGHT INTO THE BACK OF THE VAN.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The rotor disintegrates.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The back doors of the van are crushed in as the canopy, the whole front of the fuselage is HAMMERED INTO JUNK, trapping the T-1000 inside the twisted metal.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The chopper hits the pavement, flips, sideways, and cartwheels... smashing itself into a shapeless mass of twisted metal.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It falls away behind the van, tumbling end over end.
{META_DATA}: 182A Terminator fights to control the van, which is fishtailing violently
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: from the impact.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It smashes up against the center divider, screeching along the concrete, and then pulls away.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator puts the hammer down and the van accelerates.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He swerves to avoid an UGLY PICKUP crawling like a snail ahead.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: THE RIGHT FRONT FENDER of the van, crumpled by slamming the wall, is sawing into the tire.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The tire blows and peels off the clean rim.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The steel wheel grinds across the pavement, striking trails of sparks, and the van slides sideways and topples -- STEEL SCREAMS on pavement as the van grinds to a stop on its side.
{META_DATA}: 182B INSIDE THE VAN, John crawls to Sarah, who is groaning and holding her
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: bleeding leg.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She is white and shocky.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator starts to extricate himself from the crumpled driver's seat.
