{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: metal, unrecognizable.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Behind it, the TANKER TRUCK brakes hard, shuddering and groaning, trying to stop.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The big tires lock up in clouds of tire-smoke.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The rig comes to a shuddering stop just short of the wrecked chopper.
{META_DATA}: 183A The shaken DRIVER jumps down.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The behind the wreckage a cop emerges, walking toward him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: DRIVER
{DIALOGUE}: Goddamn, are you alri --
{META_DATA}: 183B SSSHHCK! T-1000 drives a blade through the man's abdomen and walks
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: on past without slowing, or even looking at him.
{META_DATA}: 183C It climbs into the open cab of the tanker. Releases the brake.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As the truck bellows are rolls forward we see the large blue letters on the side which say "CRYOCO INC.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: LIQUID NITROGEN SUPPLY'.
{META_DATA}: 184 AT THE SWAT VAN John and Terminator are carrying Sarah out of the
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: wreck.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator has the M-79 slung over his shoulder, the bandolier of grenades, and his .45 stuck in his waistband.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John has borrowed a 12-GAUGE RIOT GUN from the SWATs.
{META_DATA}: 184A The pickup they passes seconds earlier pulls up to them. The DRIVER,
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A Hispanic guy in his 50's, is getting out to help them.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator and John hear a CRASH and look back as the 185 helicopter wreckage is knocked aside by the accelerating tanker truck.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: 186 JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Holy shit.
{DIALOGUE}: Come on, Mom... we gotta keep moving... come on --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{META_DATA}: (to the pickup owner)
{DIALOGUE}: We need your truck.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The guy seems to know better than to try and stop him as Terminator slides Sarah into the front seat and climbs in behind the wheel.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John runs to the passenger side.
{META_DATA}: 187 THE TANKER ROARS, spewing smoke from its chrome stacks as it shifts
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: up through the gears.
{META_DATA}: 188 Terminator slams the pickup in gear, checking the rear-view. The
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: tanker is a hundred feet behind them now, and really moving.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator puts the throttle down, but the pickup is and old slug loaded down by a heavy home-made wooden camper-shell.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It accelerates slowly.
{META_DATA}: 189 THE TANKER slams into one end of the SWAT van, spinning it out of the
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: way with a roar and screech of twisting metal.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The 18-wheeler shifts to a higher gear, still accelerating.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 190 INT./EXT. PICKUP TRUCK
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: With the tanker right behind them, Terminator cuts the wheel, swerving the pickup back and forth across the lanes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The big rig stays right on them, it tanker whiplashing violently.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Faster!
{DIALOGUE}: He's right on us!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator doesn't reply.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He rapidly unslings the blooper, still around his neck, and reaches for a grenade.
{META_DATA}: 191 LOW ANGLE ON THE TRACTOR-TRAILER as it roars right up to the lens,
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: filling frame with chrome and lights.
{META_DATA}: 191A K-WHAM!! It rams the backs of the pickup, sending it skidding.
{META_DATA}: 191B Then the T-1000 pulls the tractor trailer up alongside the pickup and
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: crabs over, sandwiching it against the center divider.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The spinning chrome hubs tear into the passenger side door and the guard rail screeches along the other side.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The pickup bucks and shakes insanely.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It ricochets violently between the big-rig and the divider Horrible SCREECH of tortured steel.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sparks pour in sheets of fire from both sides.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The windshield shatters as the door-posts buckle in.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Metal and glass shower in through the side windows.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The frame twists and buckles.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John feels like the fillings are being shaken right out of his teeth.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The wooden camper disintegrates, falling away as kindling behind them.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 191C INT. TANKER CAB
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: T-1000 holds the wheel hard over, mercilessly grinding the pickup.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The whole rig jerks and shakes with the violence of the sustained hammering.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 191D INT./EXT. PICKUP
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator slides toward the passenger side.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Keeping his foot on the gas he lifts John over him and puts him in the driver's seat.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: Drive for a minute.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Where you going?!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator slams the shattered windshield with the palm of his hand.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Held together by the plastic laminate, the windshield flops out of its frame.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It flies over the top of the truck.
{META_DATA}: 191E Terminator pushes his upper body out over the dashboard and stands up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He turns and aims the M-79 one-handed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 191F POOM!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The grenade misses the T-1000 by less than a foot.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It EXPLODES against the front bulkhead of the tanker, almost at the top.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Liquid nitrogen pours from the opening, swept back by the 60-mph windstream.
{META_DATA}: 191G The big-rig swerves as T-1000 regains control. The tanker swings like
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: a pendulum behind the cab.
{META_DATA}: 191H The pickup accelerates, getting back out in front by a few yards.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Behind it the big-rig is trailing a swirling comet-tail of nitrogen vapor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It is gaining again.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator, still standing, opens the breech and starts to reload.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 191I John cuts across the highway and takes an OFF RAMP.
{META_DATA}: 191J T-1000 swerves the smoking behemoth across the lanes and down the
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: ramp after him, still accelerating.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It is twenty feet behind them and closing when Terminator closes the breech and FIRES.
{META_DATA}: 191K The grenade hits the front grill and EXPLODES.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The radiator is destroyed, along with half the hood.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Steam blasts out, obscuring the whole front of the truck.
{META_DATA}: 191L The semi rams the back of the pickup again. Spewing smoke and vapor
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: like some demon locomotive, the tractor-trailer pounds into the back of the pickup.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Driving it right through the intersection at the bottom of the ramp, and straight toward --
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: EXT. STEEL MILL
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The chase has led them to an area of heavy industry.
{META_DATA}: 192 THE GATES are blasted off their hinges as the semi rams the pickup
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: right through them.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator struggles to reload amid the chaos and impacts.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He has THREE GRENADES LEFT on the bandolier.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John isn't even steering.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They are just being pushed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There's nothing he can do.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They are rocketing down the broad thoroughfare which leads directly to the MAIN BUILDING of the plant.
{META_DATA}: 192A Terminator pulls himself onto the roof of the pickup.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He leaps to the bed, takes two powerful strides and -- Leaps onto the semi.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He climbs rapidly onto the hood.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 192B And FIRES POINT BLANK THROUGH THE WINDSHIELD.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Right into T-1000's face.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The EXPLOSION blows out all the glass and fills the cab with smoke and fire Terminator grabs onto the air-horn as the truck starts to SHUDDER AND 192C SCREAM.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: IT IS JACK-KNIFING.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Almost dream-slow the cab begins to swing sideways, until its tires are shrieking over the pavement.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The tractor is smashed back at right-angles to the tanker-trailer which begins to slide broadside.
{META_DATA}: 192D The juggernaut bucks and shudders as the tires and smoke sideways
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: across the pavement.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It begins to topple.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator hold on as the side of cab becomes the top.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: With an unholy scream, like the unoiled hubs of Hell, the whole rig slides on its side at 60 mph toward the steel mill.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A sheet of sparks sixty feet wide trails behind it on the pavement.
{META_DATA}: 192E John sees what's behind him, then snaps around to see the building
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: looming right in front.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The huge rolling doors are partly open.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: No choice.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He steers right through them into the mill, as --
{META_DATA}: 192F Terminator, with one second to go, leaps from the cab --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He flies through the open doors as -- The tanker hits the building and --
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 193 INT. STEEL MILL/MAIN AISLE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator slams to the floor of the mill and rolls, as -- The tanker-trailer smashed into a massive concrete support at one side of the doors.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Thunderous carnage of twisting metal.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: o 193A It splits wide open.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A river of liquid nitrogen pours out at -230.
{META_DATA}: 193B John hits the brakes, sliding out of control. He slows almost to a
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: stop but hits a steel support column head-on.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He and Sarah are slammed forward, hard.
{META_DATA}: 193C Terminator, still clutching the M-79 blooper, rolls and slides across
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: the floor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He smashes through a railing and slams up against the base of a massive machine.
{META_DATA}: 193D The semi cab swings about the trailer wreckage, into the building, and
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: shudders to a stop.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Liquid nitrogen sprays over the cab, flooding out around it in a HISSING WAVEFRONT OF ULTRACOLD.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Freezing vapor swirls everywhere, obscuring the wreck.
{META_DATA}: 193E TERMINATOR lies still. A beat. Then he rolls weakly, rising on one
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: elbow to survey the scene.
{META_DATA}: 193F IN THE WRECKED PICKUP, John stirs. He is stunned, and blood runs from
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: his nose.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dazed, he realizes he is in a steel mill.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There are sirens, and he can see men running... shouting.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He turns and sees what they are running from...
{META_DATA}: 193G The wall of nitrogen vapor spreads from the demolished tanker. It is
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: a strange vista of fire and ice.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The huge SMELTERS pour out orange light and fire from the sides of the huge galley, while the freezing vapor rolls down the center.
{META_DATA}: 193H TIGHT ON THE WRECK. A billowing gray cloud. Deep inside, the shape
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: of the cab in visible.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A FIGURE emerges, pulling itself out.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It drops to the floor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The hissing, boiling river of liquid nitrogen flows around its feet.
{META_DATA}: 194 The T-1000 staggers, moving slowly, painfully. It has finally been
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: affected by something.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Its feet are freezing to the ground as it walks...
{META_DATA}: 194A CLINK! One of its feet breaks off at a glassy angle. It stumbles
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: forward, and -- 194B Its other foot snaps off.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As it catches its balance on the stump of its other ankle, 194C the whole lower leg shatters at the impact.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It topples forward to its knees.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Catches itself on one hand.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Liquid nitrogen flows around the hand.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Now the hand is stuck to the pavement.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 194D The T-1000 pulls and... CLINK!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The hand snaps off at the wrist.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It looks stupidly at the glassy stump of a wrist.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: For the first time we see an expression on its face we know to be a true one... The expression is pain.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Agony.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Its mouth opens in a soundless scream as the hoar-frost races up its legs, across its body.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 194E And that's the position it freezes in.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It has become a statue, kneeling in the frozen vapor, that surprised look of agony frozen on its face.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The liquid nitrogen stops flowing and begins to evaporate.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 194F Terminator, just beyond the boundary of the cold, can see the T-1000 clearly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He draws his .45 and aims.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: Hasta la vista, baby.
{META_DATA}: 194G K-POW! The single shot blows the T-1000 into a million diamonds
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: spraying up into the air.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They shimmer across the ground for twenty feet in all directions.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator lowers the gun, satisfied.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks like he needs a vacation.
{META_DATA}: 195 JOHN AND SARAH have seen it from the pickup. She is in bad shape.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Conscious but very weak.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He tries the door.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's jammed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He kicks it open.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Okay, Mom, we gotta get out now, come on.
{DIALOGUE}: That's it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He helps her slide down from the seat of the truck.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her knees give way.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John has to take a lot of her weight.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He reaches in and picks up the riot gun off the seat.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They hobble toward --
{META_DATA}: 195A TERMINATOR. On his knees, he looks into the dissipating cloud of
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: vapor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The heat of the furnaces has evaporated all the liquid nitrogen.
{META_DATA}: 196 INSERT, TIGHT ON THE FLOOR - the T-1000 shards are melting,
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: liquefying.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hundreds of drops of mercury, spattered across the floor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Orange light of the enormous black-furnaces dances on liquid metal.
{META_DATA}: 197 TERMINATOR struggles to rise. One arm is shattered, the hand smashed
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: and useless.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And some leg-servos are damaged.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He can barely stand.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John and Sarah arrive.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: We don't have much time.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: What?
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator points.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John and Sarah watch as --
{META_DATA}: 198 INSERT, T-1000 DROPLETS are creeping together. Fusing into larger
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: blobs.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: These pools shiver and run together, soon forming a central mass.
{META_DATA}: 199 ON JOHN AND SARAH, realizing it's not over.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Come on!
{DIALOGUE}: Let's go!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator gets one of Sarah's arms over his shoulder and they go.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BEHIND THEM, something is moving.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 200 A HEAD is forming up out of a pool mercury.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: it rises, as shoulders form.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: hunching up from the liquid mass.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Half-formed, it turns to look straight at them.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John looks back in new terror as --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The T-1000 rises to man-height.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It is still in mercury form, but its features are forming rapidly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It takes its first step after them.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah stumbles and they pull her up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 201 Terminator himself has a pronounces limp, dragging one leg with a shattered ankle joint.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John's the one pulling, straining, driving them forward.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They round a corner into --
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 202 INT. AISLE BETWEEN FURNACES
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It is a maze of monstrous machinery.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The heat is tremendous.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The air shivers with a pounding roar.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah cries out in pain and stumbles again.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Come on, Mom, you can do it!
{DIALOGUE}: Come on!!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They drag her up, and stagger on.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her leg is bathed in blood and she is deathly pale.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He looks back.
{META_DATA}: 203 INT, MAIN GALLERY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The T-1000 steps INTO FRAME.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Fully formed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The hell-fire light glints on its impassive cop face.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It walks forward.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: At first it seems unaffected by its crystallization but --
{META_DATA}: 203A ANGLE ON ITS HAND as it touches a railing in passing. The railing is
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: covered with O.S.H.A. yellow-and-black safety tape.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The hand turns yellow and black, the color fading to normal by about the elbow.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It rips the hand from the railing with difficulty.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There is a sound like adhesive tape ripping off a surface.
{META_DATA}: 203B The T-1000 looks at its yellow-and-black striped hand. It wills the
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: hand back to normal.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We see ripples of "static" or system noise moving subtly over the surface of its body.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It's starting to "glitch".
{META_DATA}: 203C TRACKING WITH THE T-1000'S FEET. With each step, the pattern on the
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: tile floor "invades" its lower legs.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Fades as the foot is lifted.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Returns as it is set down.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The foot is trying to meld with the floor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The chameleonic function is out of control.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The T-1000 is losing it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It moves forward, searching.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It rounds the corner, entering the aisle between the furnaces.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 204 INT. AISLE
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator sees the SILHOUETTE closing on them through the smoky gleam.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The T-1000 breaks into loping run when it sees them, Terminator turns to Sarah over John.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: Keep going.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John shakes his head no.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The T-1000 is almost on them.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: RUN!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John runs, dragging, half-carrying Sarah as best he can.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She can barely stay conscious.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Half-running, delirious, she stumbles and drops to her knees.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John pulls but she can't rise.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{META_DATA}: (crying, shouting)
{DIALOGUE}: Come on, you gotta try... please, Mom.
{DIALOGUE}: Get up!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John looks back to see --
{META_DATA}: 204A TERMINATOR trying to load the M-79. With his shattered hand, he can
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: barely maneuver is last grenade into the breech.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: T-1000 smacks the weapon out of his hands.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It clatters to the floor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The grenade spins across the floor, rolling under some machinery.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator lunges, slamming the T-1000 against a wall with all his weight.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The battle is joined.
{META_DATA}: 204B JOHN AND SARAH have reached the back of the aisle. It is a cul-de-
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: sac, blocked on the end by the base of an IMMENSE SMELTER CRUCIBLE.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They turn to watch the titans battle in silhouette, backlit by the molten sparks falling from the furnaces above.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The battle which will decide their fate.
{META_DATA}: 204C Terminator grabs the T-1000 and hurls it with awesome force against
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: the opposite wall of the narrow alley.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In less time than it would take to turn, the 204D T-1000 morphs trough itself, front to back... face emerging from the back of its head.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 204E It comes off the wall straight at Terminator, who smashes his good fist into its face.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The pile-driver blow buries Terminator's fist almost to the elbow.
{META_DATA}: 204F But the T-1000's head morphs in a split-second into a hand which grips
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator's wrist, and the head "emerges" somewhere else, the geometry shifting faster than we can follow.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 204G The T-1000 slams Terminator into a large machine, jamming his arm into the moving works.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A massive sliding bar SCISSORS HIS ARM, smashing it into junk at the elbow, pinning him in the machine.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator strains against the machine pinning him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We hear his servos whining with overload.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The T-1000 turns and lopes toward Sarah and John.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah screams and hurls John into a gap between the machines.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He falls into a maze of pipes and girders.
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 205 INT. MAZE OF MACHINES
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: JOHN turns to see her in the entrance of the narrow gap.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She could follow him but she doesn't.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: SUDDENLY a dark mass moves toward him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John gasps as a huge steel counterweight, driven by a chain 6 inches thick, slides toward him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He rolls out of the way.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: When he looks back, he cannot see the opening.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Mom!
{DIALOGUE}: MOMMM!!
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 206 INT. AISLE BETWEEN FURNACES
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TERMINATOR strains to reach a 6-foot steel bar lying near him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Steel workers use them to move the red-hot ingots around.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He gets hold of the end and uses it as a lever.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: With titanic effort he spreads the massive components which are holding him, and withdraws him arm, which is severed at the elbow.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dangling junk hands from the crushed joint.
{META_DATA}: 207 SARAH has lost sight of John. It is much of a goodbye as they will
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: have.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She turns as the T-1000 closes on her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She is half-slumped against the sooty machines, looking barely conscious.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She struggles to load a shell into the empty weapon.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: At the last instant she whips up the RIOT GUN and FIRES.
{META_DATA}: A207 T-1000's face is blown open, but quickly reforms as it closes on her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She fumbles to get another shell into the magazine but -- A208 THUNK!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A steel needle slams through her shoulder, pinning her.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The polymorphic killer cocks back its other hand.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The index finger extends as a gleaming needle, toward her eye --
{CHARACTER_NAME}: T-1000
{DIALOGUE}: Call to John.
{DIALOGUE}: Now.
{META_DATA}: 207C WHAM!! SOMETHING whistles down on the T-1000 with such force that is
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: cleaves it head and body in two down to the naval.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The 6-foot steel bar is imbedded in its body.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator hurls the killer off Sarah.
{META_DATA}: 207D The T-1000 pulls the steel shaft out of itself and attacks him with
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: fury.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Swinging again and again.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Hammering Terminator back.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator falls back against the wall.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Behind the T-1000 is an enormous I-beam, hanging from two chains.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It is used to lift ingots into the smelters, and it runs on a linear track.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 207E The T-1000 grabs the I-beam and rolls it down the track.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Straight at Terminator.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The two-ton girder smashes into his chest, crushing the armor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The T-1000 pulls the I-beam back, and then heaves it forward again.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator turns and takes the second blow on the shoulder.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We hear metal crush and break inside him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He sags, turning to grip the wall... The third blow slams into his back, smashing his spine and pelvis.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We hear servos ratcheting and failing.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He drops to his knees, crucified on a wall of machinery.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The fourth blow is centered between his shoulder blades.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sound of crushing metal.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His skull is partially caved in.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He slides to the floor.
{META_DATA}: 207F ON THE T-1000, emotionless as it walks forward.
{META_DATA}: 207G TERMINATOR is a pathetic shape on the floor. He is trying to crawl,
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: feebly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Dragging his malfunctioning legs behind the crushed spine.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His arm stump screeches on the tile floor as he inches himself forward.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His exposed machine eye burns red with determination.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We see his prize.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He has the M-79, with the breech still open, cradled in the crook of his ruined arm.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He good hand, the exposed steel one, is reaching for the last grenade, which is visible under the skirt of the massive smelter base.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His metal fingers reach out for it as --
{META_DATA}: 207H The T-1000 raises the heavy steel bar over his head and stabs it down
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: with unbelievable force.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It punches into Terminator's back, through a gap in the shattered armor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The T-1000 levers it back and forth, widening the hole.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then is raises the pointed bar again and slams it down.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It punches right through.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Emerging from Terminator's chest.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And into the floor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He is pinioned.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The cyborg sags face down and stop moving.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The light goes out of his eye.
{META_DATA}: CUT TO:
{SCENE_BOUNDARY}: 208 INT. MAZE OF MACHINERY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John scuttles like a rat through the gut of the smelter.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Above him, vast machines churn untended.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He hears a voice... SARAH'S Calling low and urgent to him.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: John?
{DIALOGUE}: John?
{DIALOGUE}: Can you hear me?
{DIALOGUE}: Where are you?
{META_DATA}: 208A He crawls out of the shadows.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Onto a landing next to one of the SMELTER CRUCIBLES.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Molten steel glows bright orange in the crucible of the furnace.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Heat shimmers the air, giving everything a hallucinatory quality.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John sees Sarah nearby, limping toward him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She can barely move, her leg bathed in blood.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He runs toward her.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{META_DATA}: (gasping)
{DIALOGUE}: Help me, honey...
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TIGHT ON SARAH, her stoic face, as she hobbles forward, reaching out to him.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Something rises behind her, OUT OF FOCUS.
{META_DATA}: 209 ANOTHER, IDENTICAL, SARAH... but this one has a shotgun.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Aimed right at us.
{META_DATA}: 209A JOHN freezes. Which is which? He looks down. The first Sarah's
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: feet are melded with the floor, sucking and fusing with the tiles as she walks.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They have the color and pattern of the tiles up to the knee.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: John, get out of the way!!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{META_DATA}: (screaming)
{DIALOGUE}: SHOOT!!!!
{META_DATA}: 209B John dives aside. The Sarah-form spins, changing into you-know-who.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah starts unloading the shotgun into it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BOOM!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It staggers back.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: K-CHAK.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She chambers another round.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BOOM!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It staggers again.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: K-CHAK.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: BOOM!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And again.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And again.
{META_DATA}: 209C The T-1000 is blown back a step and Sarah advances with each shot.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The craters in the T-1000's body "heal" slowly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Its power is waning.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She FIRES again.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: And again.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Her eyes blazing with feral intensity.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She walks it back, right to the edge of the pit of MOLTEN STEEL.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: K-CHAK... CLICK.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She's empty.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The T-1000 is right at the edge.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: In a second it will recover its composure, as its crater hits close slowly.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She has failed.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Now it will kill them both, Except...
{META_DATA}: 210 CLOSEUP TERMINATOR, as the chain drive brings it into view.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Half human flesh, half chrome steel.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His red eye gazes right at us as he -- FIRES.
{META_DATA}: 210A The T-1000 takes the round in the belly. The grenade EXPLODES inside
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: its body.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A huge hole is blown clean through it, and it is ripped open and peeled back, half inside-out.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It topples into the molten steel and --
{META_DATA}: 211 The T-1000's head and upper body reappear above the molten steel.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It is screaming.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A terrifying, inhuman siren of a scream.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It is changing, morphing, transforming into anything and everything it's ever been so rapidly the eye can barely follow it -- We catch a glimpse of Janelle Voight checkered with the linoleum tile colors, Lewis the Guard with knives exploding from his face, other faces, switching at a stroboscopic rate now... a face every two frames until they merge into one face --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The T-1000 screams and slips beneath the surface of the molten steel.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We see liquid silver running in dissipating whorls over the superheated surface... until it vanishes, swirling into nothing.
{META_DATA}: 212 JOHN runs to Sarah. She stands staring into the pit. The empty
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: shotgun slips from her fingers.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Clatters to the floor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He sees that she's okay and he runs to the fallen Terminator.
{META_DATA}: 212A The crippled cyborg is trying to rise. Its servos whine and stutter.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It pathetically lifts itself to a kneeling position, collapses... tries again.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John lifts for all he's worth.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah joins them, helping.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The help the crippled machine get on its feet.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It can barely stand.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: I need a vacation.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They walk to the edge of the pit.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator looks down and sees that it is over.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{META_DATA}: (to Terminator)
{DIALOGUE}: Is it dead?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: Terminated.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John unzips Sarah's backpack and takes out the hand of the first terminator.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Will it melt in there?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: Yes.
{DIALOGUE}: Throw it in.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He does.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It sinks into the lava.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Vanishes.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: And the chip.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John takes it out of his pocket.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Looks at it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Tosses it into the smelter.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: It's finally over.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: No.
{DIALOGUE}: There is another chip.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He touches a metal finger to the side of his head.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: And it must be destroyed also.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John suddenly understands what he means.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator looks at Sarah.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They both know what must be done.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: John shakes his head.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: No!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: I'm sorry, John.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: No, no no!!
{DIALOGUE}: It'll be okay.
{DIALOGUE}: Stay with us!
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: I have to go away, John.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: Don't do it.
{DIALOGUE}: Please... don't go --
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Tears are streaming down his face.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: TIGHT CLOSEUP TERMINATOR, turning toward John.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The human side of his face is in shadow, so we see mostly the chrome skull and the red eye.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: It must end here... or I am the future.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: JOHN
{DIALOGUE}: I order you not to!
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Terminator puts his hand on John's shoulder.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He moves slightly and the human side of his face comes into the light.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He reaches toward John's face.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: His metal finger touches the tear trickling down his cheek.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: I know now why you cry.
{DIALOGUE}: But it is something I can never do.
{META_DATA}: (to both of them)
{DIALOGUE}: Goodbye.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah looks at Terminator.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Reaches out her hand to shake it.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: They lock eyes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Warriors.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Comrades.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH
{DIALOGUE}: Are you afraid?
{CHARACTER_NAME}: TERMINATOR
{DIALOGUE}: Yes.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He turns and steps off the edge.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: 213 They watch him sink into the lava.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He disappears... the metal hand sinking last... at the last second it forms into a fist with the thumb extended... a final thumbs up.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Then it is gone.
{META_DATA}: 214 HOLD ON JOHN AND SARAH, watching through the heat ripples as we --
{META_DATA}: DISSOLVE TO:
{META_DATA}: 215 THE SUN, PURE IN A CLOUDLESS SKY
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Tilting down reveal that we are in a park, very green.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: People are casually dressed, having fun.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Cycling, reading... children are playing in a playground.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Beyond the line of tree we see the skyline of Washington, D.C., with the Capital Building and the Washington Monument.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The skyline is subtly changed, with a lot of new buildings, advanced high-rises.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A CARD APPEARS
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: July 11, 2029
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: WE BOOM DOWN AND TRACK LATERALLY through a playground in the foreground.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Children swinging on swings.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sliding down slides.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Timeless things that 4 decades of technical advancement will not change.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: As we track we hear:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: August 29th 1997 came and went.
{DIALOGUE}: Nothing much happened.
{DIALOGUE}: Michael Jackson turned forty.
{DIALOGUE}: There was no Judgment Day.
{DIALOGUE}: People went to work as they always do, laughed, complained, watched TV, made love.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: We pass a jungle gym, neither melted nor burned, but full of kids swinging and yelling raucously.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Past it we drop down to see a boy pumping the pedals of a tricycle.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: I wanted to run down the street yelling... to grab them all and say "Every day form this day is a gift.
{DIALOGUE}: Use it well!"
{DIALOGUE}: Instead I got drunk.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: STILL TRACKING we come to rest on an elderly woman seated on a bench.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It is SARAH, now 64 years old.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: The world has aged her, but she seems at peace in this moment.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She speaks into a microcassette recorder.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: That was thirty years ago.
{DIALOGUE}: But the dark future which never came still exists for me, and it always will, like the traces of a dream lingering in the morning light.
{DIALOGUE}: And the war against the machines goes on.
{DIALOGUE}: Or, to be more precise, the war against those who build the wrong machines.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: There is a man in is forties playing with two small children nearby.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He turns.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It is John Connor.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Through he has the same stern features in adulthood, there is no eye-patch, no scarring.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: He is far from the haggard man on grim destiny we saw in the world that might have been.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: But there is still penetrating intelligence, even wisdom, in his eyes.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: John fights the war differently than it was foretold.
{DIALOGUE}: Here, on the battlefield of the Senate, the weapons are common sense... and hope.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: A FOUR-YEAR-OLD GIRL runs to her to have her shoelace tied.
{CHARACTER_NAME}: GIRL
{DIALOGUE}: Tie me, grandma.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Grandma Sarah smiles.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: It is the only time we have seen her smile so far.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She bends as the little girls puts her foot up on the bench.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: She ties as we hear:
{CHARACTER_NAME}: SARAH (V.O.)
{DIALOGUE}: The luxury of hope was given to me by the Terminator.
{DIALOGUE}: Because if a machine can learn the value of human life... maybe we can too.
{SCENE_DESCRIPTION}: Sarah ruffles the kids's hair as she runs off to play with her dad.
{META_DATA}: FADE OUT
